<h1><center>Exercise CARAT 96</center></h1>
<title>Exercise CARAT 96</title>
</center>
<hr>
The second Cooperation Afloat Readiness And Training cruise
(CARAT 96), supporting routine bilateral exercises with the military
forces of several nations of Southeast Asia, will take place from
April 22, to July 12, 1996.<br>
The purpose of this training cruise is to promote cooperation and goodwill, and to offer mutually
beneficial training opportunities in the region.  CARAT 96 is
another example of the U.S. Pacific Command's strategy of
cooperative engagement.<br>
A <a href="http://www.c7f.yokipc.navy.mil/">U.S. SEVENTH Fleet</a> naval task group consisting of four surface ships, one submarine, two P-3C Orion Maritime Patrol Aircraft and elements of a Marine Expeditionary Unit will participate.  The training cruise will involve approximately
1,500 U.S. Navy and Marine Corps personnel.<br>
For additional 
information regarding Exercise Cobra Gold '96, contact U.S. Pacific Command.
