<hr>

<title>Fleet Chaplain Biography</title>

<IMG SRC="condon3.jpg" ALIGN="right" align="middle" height="282" width="230">

<h1>Captain Edwin D. Condon, Jr.<br>

Chaplain Corps, U.S. Navy</h1>

<H2>U.S. Pacific Fleet Chaplain</H2>

<HR>

Captain Edwin D. Condon is a native of Boston and an

alumnus of Boston College and Saint John's Seminary.&nbsp;

He was ordained a Roman Catholic priest in 1961 and

served two parishes as a hospital chaplain.<p>

Commissioned in October 1972 as a chaplain in the U.S.

Naval Reserve, he reported for active duty in 1975 and

received his permanent appointment in the Regular Navy

in April 1979.<P>

His first duty station was at the Naval Amphibious

Base, Little Creek, Norfolk, Virginia. &nbsp;His overseas

assignment was at Marine Corps Air Station, Iwakuni,

Japan. &nbsp;Subsequent assignments have been with the

submarine community at Groton, Connecticut, the United

States Naval Academy, a tour as a Chaplain Corps

Recruiter, plankowner and Command Chaplain of the USS

THEODORE ROOSEVELT (CVN 71), and Assistant Fleet

Chaplain, U.S. Atlantic Fleet.<P>

Prior to reporting as the Fleet Chaplain, U.S. Pacific

Fleet, he was the Staff Chaplain, Chief of Naval

Education and Training in Pensacola, Florida.<P>

Decorations include Legion of Merit, the Meritorious

Service Medal with Gold Star, Navy Commendation Medal

with two Gold Stars, National Defense Service Medal,

Sea Service Deployment Ribbon, and the Navy Recruiting

Ribbon.<P>

Chaplain Condon is an honorary member of the U.S. Naval

Academy Class of 1982.

<BR><BR><BR>

