<h1><center>Naval Tradition:<br>Bell-bottom Trousers</center></h1>
<title>Navy History/Tradition/Customs</title>
</center>
<hr>
<br>
<h2>Bell-bottom Trousers</h2>
The Sailor's bell-bottom trousers, which came to epitomize '60s and early '70s fashion, are actually a practical item for Sailors living aboard ship.  The wide, flared, legs are easy to roll up when swabbing a deck or wading through slightly flooded spaces.<br><br>
<br>
