<IMG SRC="cpf_logo.gif" alt= ""align=right align=middle></hi>
<h1><center>Naval Tradition:<br>Passing Honors</center></h1>
<title>Navy History/Tradition/Customs</title>
</center>
<hr>
<br>
<h2>Passing Honors</h2>
Passing honors are ordered by 
ships and boats when vessels, embarked officials, or embarked 
officers pass (or are passed) close aboard - 600 yards for ships, 
400 yards for boats.<p>
Such honors are exchanged between ships of the U.S. Navy, between ships of the Navy and the Coast Guard, and between U.S. and most foreign navy ships passing close aboard.  "Attention" is 
sounded, and the hand salute is rendered by all persons in view 
on deck (not in ranks).<p>
<br>
