<title>Navy History/Tradition/Customs</title>
</center>
<hr>
<br>
<h2>Chewing the Fat</h2>
"God made the vittles, but the devil made the cook," was a popular saying used by seafaring men in the last century when salted beef was staple diet aboard ship.<br>
<br>
This tough cured beef, suitable only for long voyages when nothing else was as cheap or would keep as well, required prolonged chewing to make it edible.  Men often chewed one chunk for hours, just as if it were chewing gum and referred to this practice as "chewing the fat.".<br>
<br>
