<title>Navy History/Tradition/Customs</title>
</center>
<hr>
<br>
<h2>The Lucky Bag</h2>
The so-called Lucky Bag was really a huge locker in which articles lost aboard ship were deposited.  Once a month these articles were produced and handed back to their respective owners.  But there was a catch to it...each lucky recipient of a lost article was then given three strokes from the cat-o'-nine tails to teach him not to lose anything again.<br>
<br>
