<body background="chalk.jpg">
<IMG SRC="cpf_logo.gif" alt= ""align=right align=middle></hi>
<br><h1><center>Naval Tradition</center></h1>
<title>Navy History/Tradition/Customs</title>
</center>
<hr>
<br>
<h2>Jacob's Ladder</h2>
Jacob's Ladder is a portable ladder made of rope or metal and used primarily as an aid in boarding a ship.  Originally, the Jacob's Ladder was a network of line leading to the skysail on wooden ships.  The name alludes to the biblical Jacob, reputed to have dreamed that he climbed a ladder to the sky.<br>
<br>
Anyone who has ever tried climbing a Jacob's Ladder while carrying a seabag can apreciate the allusion.  It does seem that the climb is long enough to take one into the next world.<br>
<br>
