<html>
<body background="chalk.jpg">
<IMG SRC="cpf_logo.gif" alt= ""align=right align=middle></hi>
<br><h1><center>Naval Tradition</center></h1>
<title>Navy History/Tradition/Customs</title>
</center>
<hr>
<br>
<h2>Log Book</h2>
Today, any bound record kept on a daily basis aboard ship is called a "log."  Originally, records were kept on the sailing ship by inscribing information onto shingles cut from logs and hinged so they opened like books.  When paper became more readily available, "log books" were manufactured from paper and bound.  Shingles were relegated to naval museums but the slang term stuck.<br> 
<br>
