<h1><center>Pacific Fleet History</center></h1>
<title>Pacific Fleet History</title>
</center>
<hr>
<br>
<h2>The Attack on Pearl Harbor</h2>
<strong>(December 7, 1941)</strong>--At 0755, Sunday morning, the Pacific Fleet was attacked by Japanese torpedo-bombers, dive-bombers, and fighters from Japanese carriers while the U.S. fleet was at anchor in Pearl Harbor.
<p>The Japanese concentrated on the battleships anchored off Ford Island.  Among them is the battleship USS ARIZONA (BB 39), which is destroyed by a bomb that detonates her forward magazine, killing 1,103 of the 1,400 men aboard.
<hr>
