<html>
<body background="chalk.jpg">
<IMG SRC="cpf_logo.gif" alt= ""align=right align=middle></hi>
<h1><center>This Week In<br>Pacific Fleet History</center></h1>
<title>This Week In Pacific Fleet History</title>
</center>
<hr>
<br>
On April 1, 1925, Lieutenant Commander John D. Price made the first 
night landing on an American carrier on the Navy's first Aircraft Carrier, USS LANGLEY (CV 1) off San Diego, California.
<br>
<br>
<img src="/cv1pbys.gif" alt= ""align=left align=bottom><b>PBY Catalinas fly above the Navy's first Aircraft Carrier, USS LANGELY (CV-1).  LANGLEY, originally an amphibious troop ship called USS JUPITER, was converted for use as the Navy's first Aircraft Carrier in early 1922.  Fourteen years later, in 1936, LANGLEY was again converted, this time to serve as a seaplane tender.  (OFFICIAL U.S. NAVY PHOTOGRAPH)</b>
<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br>
