<h1><center>Pacific Fleet History:<br>Fleet Problem XIX</center></h1>
<title>Pacific Fleet History</title>
</center>
<hr>
<br>
<h2>April 1938: Fleet Problem XIX</h2>
In the course of this exercise, the USS SARATOGA (CV 3) launches a surprise attack on the fleet base at Pearl Harbor, foreshadowing the Japanese attack of December 1941.<br><br>
<img src="saratoga.gif"><br><h4>USS SARATOGA (CV 3), Circa 1942.  Official U.S. Navy Photo)</h4>
