<h1><center>Pacific Fleet History</center></h1>
<title>Pacific Fleet History</title>
</center>
<hr>
<br>
<h2>Battle of Coral Sea</h2>
<strong>(May 4-8, 1942)</strong>--Japanese forces suffer their first strategic defeat of World War II when the Pacific Fleet codebreakers at Pearl Harbor learn of a plan to seize Port Moresby, on the southeastern coast of New Guinea, and the island of Tulagi in the Solomons.<br>
The Tulagi landing is unopposed, but Rear Admiral Fletcher's Task Force 17, formed around USS LEXINGTON (CV 2) and USS YORKTOWN (CV 5), is on hand to intercept the Japanese units that enter the Coral Sea.<br>
The resulting action is the first carrier air battle ever fought and the first battle in Naval history where the combatant ships never came within sight of each other.<br>
<hr>
<img src="coral6.jpg"  alt= ""align=left align=bottom> USS CORAL SEA (CV-43)<br>Commissioned 1947 -<br>Decommissioned 1990<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><hr>
