<h1><center>This Week In<br>Pacific Fleet History</center></h1>
<title>This Week In Pacific Fleet History</title>
</center>
<hr>
<br>
<h2>June 29, 1966: Cripple<br>North Vietnam's Energy Supply</h2>
Forty-six planes from USS CONSTELLATION (CVA 64) and USS RANGER (CVA 61) strike oil storage plants on the outskirts of Hanoi and Haiphong, beginning a campaign to cripple the petroleum, oil, storage and distribution system of North Vietnam.  This is the nearest American bombs have fallen to either city.<br>
