</center>
<hr>
<br>
<h2>August 23, 1950:<br>Tokyo Conference</h2>
In a dramatic conference in Tokyo, General MacArthur persuades Admiral Forrest P. Sherman, the Chief of Naval Operations, and General J. Lawton Collins, Army Chief of Staff, to support his plan for an amphibious assault at Inchon, on the west coast of Korea.<br>
<br>
