<br>
<h2>August 29, 1952:<br>"All United Nations Air Effort"</h2>
Planes from the carriers USS BOXER (CV21) and USS ESSEX (CV 9) participated in the biggest bombing raid in the Korean War.  More than 1,000 U.N. aircraft attacked Pyongyang, the North Korean capital.<br>
<br>
