<h1><center>This Week In<br>Pacific Fleet History</center></h1>
<title>This Week In Pacific Fleet History</title>
</center>
<hr>
<br>
<h2>September 1, 1942:<br>Seabees</h2>
The 6th Naval Construction Battalion arrives at Guadalcanal, thereby becoming the first Seabee unit to enter a combat zone.  The Seabees, who performed sterling service throughout the Pacific War, were organized by Rear Admiral Ben Moreell, Chief of the Bureau of Yards and Docks, in October 1941.<br>
<br>
<hr>
