<hr>
<br>
<h2>September 2, 1945:<br>The War is Over!</h2>
The Japanese instrument of surrender was signed aboard the battleship USS MISSOURI (BB 63) in Tokyo Bay.  General Douglas MacArthur signed on behalf of the Allied Powers.  Fleet Admiral Chester W. Nimitz signed on behalf of the United States.<br>
<br>
