<h2>September 29, 1945:<br>USS NEW JERSEY in Vietnam</h2>
USS NEW JERSEY (BB 62) begins operations off the coast of Vietnam, firing 20- and 16-inch shells at enemy postions northwest of Con Thien near the northern boundary of the De-Militarized Zone.<br>
