<IMG SRC="cpf_logo.gif" alt= ""align=right align=middle></hi>
<h1><center>This Week In<br>Pacific Fleet History</center></h1>
<title>Pacific Fleet History</title>
</center>
<hr>
<br>
<h2>October 6-7, 1943:<br>Battle of Vella LaVella</h2>
Another night action takes place in the Solomons when the Japanese send a force of nine destroyers and 12 small craft under Rear Admiral Matsuji Ijuin to evacuate the 600 troops on Vella LaVella.  It is intercepted by six destroyers commanded by Captain Frank R. Walker.<br>
<br>
One destroyer is sunk on each side -- USS CHEVALIER (DD 451), commanded by Lieutenant Commander George R. Wilson, and HIJMS Yugumo -- plus two American destroyers are damaged.  The Japanese small craft extricate the island's garrison.  This is the last engagement fought in the central Solomons.<br>
<br>
<hr>
