<h1>Japanese helicopter catches fire<br>
on the ground at NAS Barbers Point</h1>
<hr>
<strong>Barbers Point, HI., June 17, 1996</strong> -- At approximately 2 p.m., Monday, June 17, a Japanese SH-60 helicopter landed at Naval Air Station, Barbers Point, and was taxiing on the ground when the helo caught fire.  All crew members and passengers, a total of eight people, walked away from the accident.  There were no major injuries reported.<br>
The helicopter is assigned to the JDS Hiei and is in Hawaii as part of RIMPAC exercises.  The helicopter’s crew members followed safety procedures resulting in minimal injury.  The incident is under investigation by the Japanese Maritime Self-Defense Force (JMSDF).<br>
Released by MSO and JMSDF Liaison for RIMPAC ‘96, 17 June 1996.  Point of Contact: LCDR Shibata or LCDR Ishihara, 474-6210.<br>
<br>
<br><br><br>
<center>-USN-</center>
