<html>
<body background="chalk.jpg">
<img src="rimpac4.gif"  alt= ""align=left align=middle height=191 width=250>
<title>RIMPAC 96</title>

<h1>RIMPAC 96</h1>
<hr>
<strong>(Pentagon-6 May, 1996)</strong>--Six Pacific nations will participate in Exercise RIMPAC 96, a major
maritime exercise in the vicinity of Hawaii beginning May 22.  Exercise participants include maritime forces from Australia, Canada, Chile, Japan, the Republic of Korea, and the United States.<br>
They will conduct multi-national and bi-lateral, combined training operations from May 22 through June 21, 1996.  More than 44
ships, 250 aircraft and 30,000 Sailors, airmen, Marines, soldiers and
Coast Guardsmen will be involved in this regularly-scheduled exercise.<br>
The purpose of this exercise is to improve coordination and interoperability of combined and joint forces in maritime tactical and theater operations.  RIMPAC 96 is the 15th in a series of Pacific naval exercises conducted every second year.<br>
For additional information, contact Commander Jack Papp or Lieutenant
Commander Richard Marin at the THIRD Fleet Public Affairs Office in San Diego at (619) 545-2523.  Inquiries after May 15, 1996 should be referred to the RIMPAC Combined Information Bureau (CIB) at Naval Station Pearl Harbor, Hawaii, at (808) 474- 6210.<br>
Information on RIMPAC 96 can also be obtained by contacting the RIMPAC 96 Web Site through <strong>www.cpf.navy.mil</strong>.  Releases and additional information will be provided via this Internet site as they become available.<br>
<br>
<br>
<center>-USN-</center>
<br>
