<html>
<body background="chalk.jpg">
<img src="rimpac4.gif"  alt= ""align=left align=middle height=191 width=250>
<title>RIMPAC 96 Media Events</title>
<h1>U.S. Pacific Fleet's <br>Rim of the Pacific 1996<br>
Media Events<br>
</h1>
<em><hr>Note: Nearly all coverage requires advanced coordination to ensure inclusion and transportation arrangements (seating is limited for events at sea).   The dynamics of the exercise could cause schedule changes which will be posted immediately.  Also, other coverage opportunities may emerge as the exercise unfolds.</em><br>
<hr><strong>Background information and daily updates are available to media through the Internet web site at www.cpf.nav.mil.  Media should contact the Combined Information Bureau in Pearl Harbor at (808) 474-6210.  This coverage list will be updated at least daily beginning 25 May.</strong>
<br>
<hr>
<strong>Because of the length of this document, we have hyperlinked to the following sub-headings:</strong><BR>
<ul>
<li><A HREF=#20May-17June>20 May - 17 Jun</a>
<li><A HREF=#23May>23 May</a>
<li><A HREF=#1-3June>1-3 June</a>
<li><A HREF=#3-4June>3-4 June</a>
<li><A HREF=#7June>7 June</a>
<li><A HREF=#8June>8 June</a>
<li><A HREF=#9June>9 June</a>
<li><A HREF=#11June>11 June</a>
<li><A HREF=#12June>12 June</a>
<li><A HREF=#13June>13 June</a>
<li><A HREF=#14June>14 June</a>
<li><A HREF=#14-15June>14 - 15 June</a>
<li><A HREF=#15June>15 June</a>
<li><A HREF=#16June>16 June</a>
<li><A HREF=#16-17June>16 - 17 June</a>
</ul>
<hr>
<a name="20May-17June"></a><h3>20 May - 17 June</h3>
<ul>
<li>Meterological & Oceanographic Center:  Tours, interviews concerning the center's contribution to naval operations, including demonstration of advanced technology and techniques can be arranged. 
<ul>
<li>Transportation: None required
<li>Media: Discovery Channel
</ul></ul>
<br>
<a name="23May"></a><h3>23 May</h3>
<ul>
<li>Landing craft practice at Kaneohe Bay: Both afloat and ashore coverage of AAV/LCAC practice is planned. Helos will be used in afloat portion; 25 seats. 
</ul>
<br>
<a name="1-3June"></a><h3>1-3 June</h3>
<ul>
<li>USS Kamehameha underway: SEALS operating from submarine.
<ul>
<li>Transportation: None, <strong>3 seats (already filled)</strong>
</ul></ul>
<br>
<a name="3-4June"></a><h3>3-4 June</h3>
<ul>
<li>MISSILEX at PMRF Barking Sands, Kauai:  As many as a dozen ships will participate in missile and gun firing exercises at PMRF range.  Transportation will be arranged to PMRF and then helo to ships on the evening of 3 June with return on the evening of 4 June.<strong>  25 seats (3 seats max to each ship; 6 seats filled).</strong>
<li><strong>Note:  Possible ships to view from Cowpens, Reid (both ships have agreed to provide their helos).  The following require coordination:  Antietam, Perth, Newcastle, Sydney, Huron, Algonquin, Regina, Cushing, Winnepeg, Cheju.</strong>
</ul><br>
<a name="7June"></a><h3>7 June</h3>
<ul>
<li>USS Rainier replenishment at sea:  USS Rainier will resupply several ships at sea throughout the day.  Good opportunity for coverage of logistics support at sea.  Transportation is via helo from Oahu, <strong>10 seats (6 seats filled).</strong>
</ul>
</ul><br>
<a name="8June"></a><h3>8 June</h3>
<ul>
<li>USS Kitty Hawk embark opportunities including flight operations.   <strong>20-40 seats.</strong>  
<ul><li>Transportation: fly from Oahu, 
<li>20-40 for USS Kitty Hawk
</ul>
<li>P-3 Canadian/Australian/US:  Early morning flight to observe anti-submarine mission.  Current physiology required,<strong>Full</strong>
<li>Navy Maritime Interdiction Operation (MIO): Boarding of a ship on the high seas to inspect cargo and ascertain intentions to prevent transporting of contraband.  
<ul><li>T<strong>ransportation is helo from Oahu (75 miles) Full. Requires additional coordination.</strong>
</ul>
<li>Mine clearing for transit by Bilateral Force:  Preparations for transit using Mobile Inshore Underwater Warfare (MIUW) reserve unit and surface ships to clear the channel for Freedom of Navigation transit.<br>
Transportation will be via COD to PMRF Barking Sands.  Coverage opportunity of reserve contribution to exercise with land-based unit at PMRF<strong> (20-30 seats)</strong>.  Others could go to ships using helo det onboard ship <strong>(2-3 seats per ship, possibly 3 ships involved).</strong>
</ul>
<a name="9June"></a><h3>9 June</h3>
<ul>
<li>USS Kitty Hawk defends against air attack: Coverage opportunity is for air operations in defense against attack.  Opportunity includes other stories about life aboard aircraft carrier and is for daylight only.  Depart Oahu at first light, return in afternoon. Transportation will be via COD to carrier<strong>Full.</strong> Note:  There is limited access during the training phase for Kitty Hawk.
<ul>
<li>Transportation: COD, <strong>Full</strong>.
</ul>
<li>Marine Maritime Interdiction Operation (MIO):  Boarding of a ship on the high seas to inspect cargo and ascertain intentions to prevent transporting of contraband.  
<ul><li>Transportation is helo from Oahu, <strong>Full</strong>.
</ul></ul>
<a name="11June"></a><h3>11 June</h3>
<ul>
<li>Non-combatant Evacuation Operation (NEO):  This event is an evacuation of about 100 people from an embassy under siege at Kaneohe Bay.  Media coverage opportunities are from ashore and afloat.<br>
Muster 0845 at the main gate.<br>
<li>Embark Japanese ships:  Opportunities are being coordinated with JMSDF.  More information will be made available when details are confirmed.  Probably will involve transportation via COD to PMRF Barking Sands and then JMSDF helos transfer to ships and return.<br>
Note:  One embark event is being scheduled by LCDR Ishihara, JMSDF. Available for international media. Daylight only and more details to be coordinated.
<li>USS Independence defends against air attack:  Daylight only embark for media coverage of air operations and life aboard carrier.  Transportation is via 2 CODs (aboard 1000-1100, depart late afternoon) with <strong>up to 40 seats</strong>.   
<li>Explosive Ordnance Disposal in Pearl Harbor: Several disposal demonstrations will be offered on Oahu, depending on media interest.  One demonstration is planned for this day.<ul><li>Transportation: None</ul>
</ul>
<a name="12June"></a><h3>12 June</h3>
<ul>
<li>Air cushion landing craft:  LCAC operations at sea only (no landing).  Transportation will be via USN helos from USS Essex,<strong> 10-20 seats (5 seats filled).</strong>
<ul>
<li>Transportation: USN helos from Essex
</ul>
</ul>
<a name="13June"></a><h3>13 June</h3>
<ul>
<li>Cowpens underway (Aegis air defense in ops): The thundering herd fends off attack.  
<ul><li>Transportation: HSL Det onboard picks up from Kauai, 14 Jun transfer to Essex,<strong> 3 seats</strong>
</ul>
<li>CONSOL transfer fuel from civilian tanker:  Transfer of fuel at sea from civilian tanker to USNS Diehl.  
<ul>
<li>Transportation: need helo trans, <strong>3 seats</strong></ul>
</ul>
<a name="14June"></a><h3>14 June</h3>
<ul>
<li>Embark in USS Independence:  Opportunity to view air operations (daylight only), plus gather stories about life aboard a carrier. Transportation will be via 2 CODs,<strong> 40 seats (12 filled).</strong>
</ul>
<a name="14-15June"></a><h3>14 - 15 June</h3>
<ul>
<li>Amphibious landing at PMRF Barking Sands:  Amphibious Ready Group (ARG - USS Essex, Cleveland & Harpers Ferry) execute amphibious landing of Marine Expeditionary Unit (11th MEU) using air cushion landing craft (LCAC), AAV and LCU craft.  Coverage opportunities include LCAC and AAV/LCU embarks, real-time video being transmitted to PMRF Barking Sands and USS Essex, and two CV's support amphibious landing (air ops).  Transportation will be via COD to Barking Sands, then helo. Some media can embark ARG 13 June and others 14 June,<strong> 40 seats (26 filled).</strong> 
</ul>
<a name="15June"></a><h3>15 June</h3>
<ul>
<li>PACEN underway on Rainier:  Navy Public Affairs Center onboard from Antietam to gather stories on crew.  Transportation: HSL Det,<strong> 3 seats (filled)</strong>
<li>Major A-6 formation from USS Independence:  Perhaps the last tactical flight of the Intruder. CIB is working to get two aircraft (F-16 and/or CF-18 chase planes) to support internal and external media aerial coverage.  Full flight physiology required.  <strong>Full</strong></ul>
<a name="16June"></a><h3>16 June</h3>
<ul>
<li>Indy embark:  Japanese media have requested through LCDR Ishihara a daylight only (no flight ops sked) embark aboard Indy with bounce to JDS Hiei.  Transportation: USN helo to Indy AM, depart early afternoon via JMSDF helo to Hiei, <strong>10 seats (Full).</strong>
</ul>
<a name="16-17June"></a><h3>16 - 17 June</h3>
<ul>
<li>Photo opportunities:  At the end of the exercise three photo opportunities are being planned by C3F to include a six ship armada representing each participating nation; amphibious forces with principle ships, LCAC/AAV, and air assets; and dissimilar aircraft formations.  These may be staged on different days.  Transportation: Need 2 HH46 helos for each photo opportunity.
</ul>
<br><br><br><br>
<center>-USN-</center>
<br>
<br>
