<h1>Adm. Clemins incoming CINCPACFLT<br>
Change of Command Ceremony</h1>
<title>Adm. Clemins incoming Ceremony</title>
<hr><br>
<img src="clembye.gif" alt="Adm. Clemins Leaving Ceremony" align="left" height=375 width=300>
<strong>(November 7, 1996)</strong> -- "I come to this job with a great sense of gratitude to Adm. Zlatoper and a great awareness of the legacy which I am inheriting," said Adm. Archie Clemins as he took over command of the Navy's Pacific Fleet from Adm. R. J. Zlatoper.  "This is the job to which Adm. Chester W. Nimitz came during World War II.  Our future will be a time of great challenge, and it will also be a time of bold experimentation, where we must think anew while we continue to make the Navy a place where the best and proud serve, and we accomplish the
mission to the standards of excellence set by Adm. Nimitz." (Official U.S. Navy Photo by JO1 Robert Benson)<br><br><br><br><br><br>
<hr>
