<body background="chalk.jpg">
<img src="rimpac2.gif" alt= "" align=left align=middle height=290 width=379>
<br><br>
<h1>RIMPAC 96<BR>Multi-National Force:<BR>USS PRINCETON<br>(CG 59)</h1>
<br><br><br>
<title>USS PRINCETON (CG 59)</title>
<hr>
<img src="cg59.gif" alt= "" align=right align=middle height=256 width=400>
<h1>USS PRINCETON<br>(CG 59)</h1>
USS PRINCETON is one of the most advanced combatant ships in the U.S. Pacific Fleet, incorporating some of the most advanced technology employed in any armed force today.  PRINCETON introduced to the fllet the Baseline 3 AEGIS Combat System, with its AN/SPY-1B radar system and numerous other upgrades.  She was designed to lead the surface forces of the U.S. Navy well into the 21st century.<br>
<pre><strong>Ship's Characteristics</strong>
Length.....................................567 feet
Draft (navigation)..........................33 feet
Beam........................................55 feet
Displacement..............................9600 tons
Speed.......................................30+ knots
Draft (keel)................................24 feet

<strong>Accommodations</strong>
Officers....................................37	
Chief Petty Officers........................45
Enlisted...................................327
 
<strong>Prospulsion</strong>
4 LM2500 Gas Turbine Engines 80,000 Shaft Horsepower
3 Gas TurbineGenerators 450 V, 3 phase 60Hz 4000 Amps
2 Controllable Reversible Pitch Propellers 
2 Rudders

<strong>Sensors</strong>
1 AN/SPY-1B Radar (Four Arrays)
1 AN/SPS-49 Air Search Radar
1 AN/SPS-55 Surface Search Radar
1 AN/SPQ-9 Surface Surveillance and Tracking Radar
4 AN/SPG-62 Illuminators
1 AN/SQS 53B Sonar
1 AN/SLQ-32(V)3 Electronic Warfare Suite
1 AN/SPS-64 Surface Search Radar
1 AN/SQR-19 Towed Array Sonar

<strong>Weapons</strong>
1 MK7 Mod 5 Aegis Weapons System
2 MK 45 5"/54 Caliber Lightweight Gun Mounts
2 Vertical Launch Missile Systems (VLS)
2 Harpoon Missile Quad-Cannister Launchers
2 MK 32 Mod 14 Torpedo Tubes
1 MK 15 Mod 12 Close In Weapon System (CIWS)
1 MK 36 Mod 2 Super Rapid-Blooming Off Board Chaff System
4 50 Caliber Machine Guns
4 M60 Machine Guns
2 25MM Machine Guns
2 SH-60B LAMPS MK lll Helicopters
</pre>
<br>
<h5>Source: - U.S. THIRD FLEET</h5><br>
