<html>
<body background="chalk.jpg">
<img src="rimpac4.gif"  alt= ""align=left align=middle height=191 width=250>
<h1>Rear Admiral<br>
Hideaki Kaneda, JMSDF<br>
Commander,<br>
Escort Flotilla Four</h1>
<hr>
Rear Admiral Hideaki Kaneda is a native of Kanagawa Prefecture and attended the National Defense Academy graduating with the class of 1968.  He was commissioned Ensign in 1969.<br>
His first assignment was as Assistant Communication Officer in JDS TERUZUKI (DD 162) and later as Assistant Gunnery Officer.  In 1971, he assumed duties as Instructor of JMSDF Officer Candidate School.<br>
Returning to sea, Rear Admiral Kaneda got on board JDS KATORI (TV 3501) as Assistant Training Staff of Training Squadron.  From 1973 to 1977 he served as Gunnery Officer in JDS TOKACHI (DE 218) and JDS TACHIKAZE (DDG 168).<br>
In 1983, Rear Admiral Kaneda served as Weapons Officer in JDS SHIRANE (DDH 143)  In 1984, he assumed duties in MSO Systems Programs Division.  In August 1986 he assumed command of JDS AKIGUMO (DD 121).<br>
In 1987, Rear Admiral Kaneda was selected to attend the Naval Command College, Senior International Course at the Naval War College, in Newport, Rhode Island.  Graduating with distinction, he assumed duties in MSO as Staff in Plans and Programs Division.  He successively assigned as Chief of Plans and Policy Section.<br>
In 1991, took command of Escort Division SIXTY-ONE homeported in Yokosuka.  Following this tour, he served as Head of Plans and Programs Division, MSO. In 1993, Rear Admiral Kaneda reported to Chief of Staff, Maizuru District Headquarters. Rear Admiral Kaneda reported to his present assignment as Commander, Escort Flotilla Four in June 1995.<br>
Rear Admiral Kaneda and his wife Yuuko have two sons, Hidehiro and Syuusuke.<br>
<br><br><br>
<center>-USN-</center>
<br>
