<html>

<title>CO, USS ()</title>

<body background="chalk.jpg">
<center><h1>Commodore<br>
T.H. Cox, AM, RAN</h1>
<h2>Commodore,<br>
Flotillas, Royal Australian Navy</h2></center>
<hr>
Commodore Timothy Cox was born in Sydney and educated at the Sydney Church of England Grammar School prior to entering the Royal Australian Naval College in 1962.<br>
On graduating from the RAN College in 1965 initial sea training was undertaken in HMA Ships SYDNEY  and DERWENT.  In 1966 to 67 he attended Britannia Royal Naval College Dartmouth, England which was followed by a year's training with the Royal Navy in the Portsmouth area.<br>
On return to Australia he served in HMA Ships DUCHESS, LADAVA, BOMBARD and  ANZAC prior to returning to the UK in 1972 to HMS DRYAD to join the first Principle Warfare Officers (ASW) Course.  This was followed by a posting to the RAN Tactical School as the ASW Specialist.<br>
Between 1982 to 86 he served in Canberrra in the New Surface Combatant Project (now ANZAC frigate) and attended the JSSC.  This was followed by a posting in command of HMAS DERWENT in Western Australia and then, on promotion to Captain, a posting as the Chief Staff Officer (Operations) to the Maritime Commander.  In 1990 he was posted in command of HMAS PERTH and then joined ADFWC as Commandant in February 1992.<br>
He joined Maritime Headquarters as Commodore Flotillas in January 1995.<br>
Commodore Cox is married with two children and resides in Sydney.<br>
<br>
<br>
