<html>

<title>CO, USS ()</title>

<body background="chalk.jpg">
<img src="pfg07co.gif" alt=""ALIGN=RIGHT ALIGN=MIDDLE width=280 height=363>
<h1>Cristian Gantes Young<br>
Captain, Chilean Navy</h1>
<h2>Commanding Officer,<br>
CS LYNCH (PFG 07)</h2>
Captain Gantes is the current Commanding Officer of PFG "ALMIRANTE LYNCH".  He was born in Valparasio, Chile, on 13th, 1954.  He graduated from the Chilean Naval Academy in December 1972.  After the completion of his eight month instruction aboard the training ship "ESMERALDA", he reported to the squadron and served for two years on DD "COCHRANE" and ATF "ALDEA".<br>
As a Lieutenant  JG. He attended the Naval Specialty School where he earned a Bachelor of Science in Electronic Engineering.  Later he was reassigned to the squadron and served in various ships including DD "PROTALES", DLG "PRAT" and DDG "WILLIAMS".<br>
In 1983, Captain Gantes reported to the Third Naval Zone in the Magallanes Region and served for three years on the missile boat LM "CHIPANA",  from 1987 to 1989 he served in the weapons directorate as the Electronic Systems Department Head.  In January 1990, he assumed command of the missile boat "CHIPANA" and operated from Cape Horn to the northern border.<br>
In 1991, he was selected to attend the Chilean Naval War College, Senior Course.  Graduating with honors.  In 1992 was assigned to the Programs, Research and Development Directorate as Programs Head.<br>
In 1994 he was assigned as Chilean Liaison Officer  to the Commander in Chief, U.S. Atlantic  Fleet, Norfolk, Virginia.<br>
Captain Gantes awards include the "11 of September" Medal, the "10 Years Embarked" Medal, "Minerva" and "Cruz de Malta" Medals, Colombian "Francisco Jose de Cladas", United States of America "Navy Commendation" Medal, the Naval War College Ribbon and various service related medals, he was awarded the "President of the Republic" medal for graduating first in his class at the Chilean War College, Senior course.<br>
Captain Gantes assumed his Current Position on January 12th and was promoted to his current rank in April 1996.<br>
He is married to the former Virginia Pinto and they have one son, Tomas, and three daughters Camila, Antonia, and Valentina.<br>
<br>
