<!--Code N00pa2b-->
<!--phone: (808) 471-3769-->
<!--e-mail: u00pa2b@cpf-emh.cpf.navy.mil-->
<html>

<title>Commander, Amphibious Squadron FIVE</title>

<body background="chalk.jpg">
<img src="phibron5.gif" alt=""ALIGN=RIGHT ALIGN=MIDDLE width=280 height=363></h1>
<h1>William J. Marshall, III<br>
Captain, USN</h1>
<h2>Commander,<br>
Amphibious Squadron FIVE</h2>
Captain Marshall, a graduate of Villanova University, was 
commissioned in December 1972 via the NROTC program. His 
early sea tours included the guided missile destroyer USS 
Sampson (DDG 10), homeported in Athens, Greece, and the 
frigate USS Aylwin (FF 1081), followed by his tour as First 
Lieutenant, USS Manitowoc (LST 1180). Subsequent sea tours 
were as Executive Officer, USS Saginaw (LST 1188) and 
Commanding Officer, USS Germantown (LSD 42). He assumed command of Amphibious Squadron Five in August 1995.<br>
During his first amphibious community tour Captain Marshall participated in the initial landing of US Marines in Beirut, Lebanon, in 1982, in their support as part of the Multi-National Peacekeeping Force, 
and in their final extraction two years later. In the fall of 1983 he participated in Operation Urgent Fury during the Grenada campaign, including two amphibious assault landings. On December 1, 1990, 
Captain Marshall, commanding GERMANTOWN, departed San Diego on a nine month deployment as part of the thirteen ship Amphibious Task Force supporting Operations Desert Shield and Desert Storm. Operating her four Landing Ship, Air Cushion (LCAC) amphibious assault craft, GERMANTOWN landed embarked 5th Marine Expeditionary Brigade troops and equipment ashore south of Kuwait City, February 24, 1991 -the major amphibious landing of the Gulf conflict.<br>
Captain Marshall's shore duties include assignment as Warfare Instructor at Surface Warfare Officers School, Newport, Rhode Island, Flag Secretary to Commander, Naval Surface Force Atlantic, Norfolk, Virginia, and as Special Assistant to the Vice Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff.<br>
He holds a Masters of Science Degree in Financial Management from the Naval Postgraduate School, Monterey, California and a Master of Arts Degree in National Security and Strategic Studies from the Naval War College, Newport, Rhode Island. Captain Marshall's personal decorations include the 
Defense Superior Service medal, Legion of Merit, and Defense Meritorious Service medal.<br>
Captain Marshall and his wife Tricia live in Coronado, California, with their three children, Kelly, Katie and Bud. <br>
<br>
<br>
