<br><br>
<h1>RIMPAC 96<BR>Multi-National Force:<BR>USS KITTY HAWK<br>(CV 63)</h1>
<br><br><br>
<title>USS KITTY HAWK (CV 63)</title>
<hr>
<img src="cv63.gif" alt= "" align=right align=middle height=267 width=388>
<h2>USS KITTY HAWK<br>(CV 63)</h2>
An Aircraft Carrier is often desciribed as a floating city. With a crew of more than  5,000 men, USS KITTY HAWK's population is larger than many of thc towns and cities its crew grew up in.<br>
To run K1TTY HAWK requires an infrastructure similar to a city. The duties of the Commanding Of ficer (CO) parallel those of a Mayor. He is ultimately responsible for the welfare of the ship and its crew, and establishes the guldelines under which the ship operates. Next comes the Executive Of ficer (XO), similar in many respects to a City Manager. The XO ensures the CO's guidelines are implemented and the daily functions run smoothly. The ship is further divided into 18 departments that provide the range of services required to support that large a population.<br>
<br>
<strong>USS KITTY HAWK's "Vital Statistics"</strong>
<pre>
Keel laid....................................December 27, 1956
Launched.....................................May 21, 1960
Commissioned.................................April 29, 1961
Length.......................................1,065 feet
Width........................................273 feet
Draft........................................36 feet
Average displacement.........................81,000 tons
Waterline to the flight deck.................61 feet
Waterline to the bridge......................99 feet
Total height above waterline.................201 feet
Total number of decks and levels (floors)....Eight decks and 11 levels
Speed........................................30+ knots
Engines......................................four
Boilers......................................eight
Electrical system capacity...................14,000,000 watts
Water distilling capability..................4,000,000 gallons
Anchors......................................Two (30 tons each)
Weight of anchor links ......................360 pounds each
Maxium length of anchor chain................1,080 feet
Normal number of mooring lines...............14
Propellers...................................Four (21 feet wide)
Rudders......................................Two (50 tons each)
Total number of compartments and spaces......2,400+
Aircraft capacity............................75 plus
Flight deck area.............................4.1 acres 
Hanger bay area..............................1.6 acres
Number of catapults..........................Four, steam-powered
Catapult length..............................263 feet
Effective landing area.......................120 feet
Aircraft elevators...........................four
Elevator lifting capacity....................130,000 pounds each
Crew.........................................2,800
                                             (5,300 with air wing embarked)
Average annual payroll.......................$63,000,000
Dining facilities............................seven
Meals served daily...........................6,000+
                                             (17,000 with air wing embark)
Doctors and surgeons........................ four
Operating rooms and triage areas.............six
Hospital beds................................65
Dentist......................................five
Dentist chairs...............................five
Lawyers......................................two
Convenience stores...........................four
Barber shops.................................two
Laundry......................................one
Telephones...................................2,400
</pre>
KITTY HAWK also has a 69-man security force, a 300 man public works force, a ship-wide, closed circuit television system and holds services for several denominations.

