<br>
<h1>RIMPAC 96<BR>Multi-National Force:<BR>USS COWPENS<br>(CG 63)</h1>
<br><br>
<title>USS COWPENS (CG 63)</title>
<hr>
<center><h2>USS COWPENS (CG 63)</h2><br></center>
<img src="/cg63.gif" alt= ""align=right align=middle height=205 width=396>
USS COWPENS is truly the warship of the future.  With its unmatched weapons systems, it is capable of launching offensive cruise missile strikes, coordinating airborne war at sea strikes, or protecting a carrier battle group from air, surface, or subsurface threats.<br>
In today's ever-changing environment, the ability to respond rapidly and effectively is the key to success.  At the center of USS COWPENS' capability is the AEGIS weapons system.  The AEGIS Command and Decision System is able to integrate and correlate the imputs of the ship's sensors as well as external sources.  This includes COWPENS' SPY 1-B phased array radar, which is capable of tracking over 200 tracks at ranges over 200 nautical miles.  All this makes USS COWPENS uniquely suited to serve as an area Anti-Air Warfare Commander.<br>

<pre><b>Ship's Characteristics</b>
Length............................................567 feet
Beam...............................................55 feet
Speed..............................................30+ knots
Draft (keel).......................................24 feet
Draft (navigation).................................34 feet
Displacement....................................9,600 tons

<b>Accommodations</b>
Officers...........................................33
Chief Petty Officers...............................33
Enlisted Men......................................339
Total.............................................405

<b>Propulsion</b>
4 LM 2500 Gas Turbines, 80,000 Shaft Horsepower
2 Controllable Reverse Pitch Propellers
2 Rudders

<b>Sensors</b>
1 AN/SPY-lB Phased Array Radar (Four Arrays)
1 AN/SPS-49 (V) 7 Air Search Radar
1 AN/SPS-55 Surface Search Radar
1 AN/SPS-64 (V) Navigation Radar
1 AN/SPQ-9 Surface Surveillance and Tracking Radar
4 AN/SPG-62 Fire Control Illuminators
1 AN/SQS-53B Sonar
1 AN/SQR-l9 Towed Array Sonar
1 AN/SLQ-32A (V) 3 Electronic Warfare Suite

<b>Weapons</b>
1 MK 7 Mod 5 Aegis WEapons system
1 MK 37 Mod 0 Tomahawk Weapon System
2 MK 45 5"154 Caliber Lightweight Gun Mounts
2 Harpoon Missile Quad-Cannister Launchers
2 MK 32 Mod 14 Torpedo Launchers
1 MK 15 Mod 12 Close-In Weapons System (2 mounts)
1 MK 36 Mod 6 Super Rapid-Blooming Off Board Chaff System
1 AN/SLQ-25 Underwater Weapon System
4 50 Caliber Machine Guns
2 SH-60B LAMPS MK III Helicopters

<b>Command and Control</b>
MK 1 Mod 1 Aegis Display Group
MK 1 Mod 2 Command and Decision System

Launched: 11 March 1989 at Bath Iron Works, Bath, ME.
Commissioned: 09 March 1991 at Charleston, SC.
Home Port: San Diego. CA.
</pre>
<br>
