<img src="rimpac2.gif" alt= "" align=left height=290 width=379>
<br><br>
<h1>RIMPAC 96<BR>Multi-National<br>Force:<BR><br>USS CUSHING (DD 985)</h1>
<br><br><br>
<title>USS CUSHING (DD 985)</title>
<hr>
<h2>USS CUSHING <br>(DD 985)</h2>
USS CUSHING (DD 985) is the twenty-third SPRUANCE Class Destroyer to be designed and built by Ingalls Shipbuilding Division of Litton Industries in Pascagoula, Mississippi.  Homeported in Pearl Harbor, Hawaii, CUSHING is assigned to Naval Surface Group Middle Pacific.<br>
The Spruance Class Destroyer is unique among U.S. warships because it is the first major class to be powered solely by gas turbine engines.  CUSHING is driven by four General Electric LM-2500 gas turbines turning twin controllable reversible pitch propellers.  Designed originally for use on large aircraft, these engines have been modified for marine use and produce approximately 20,000 horsepower each.  They are capable of moving the ship at speeds in excess of 30 knots and provide a degree of maneuverability and flexibility unequaled by any other warship of similar size.<br>
Built with future growth in mind, CUSHING's design is modular in nature, allowing for easy installation of entire subsystems within the ship.  Space and power reservations have been made to accommodate future weapons and electronic systems as they are developed.  This design feature will allow CUSHING to adapt as new military technology evolves.<br>
As a highly versatile multi-mission destroyer, CUSHING is capable of operating independently or in company with amphibious or carrier task forces.  Although equipped to handle a wide variety of tasks, CUSHING's primary mission is Anti-Submarine Warfare (ASW).  CUSHING's primary mission is Anti-Submarine Warfare (ASW).  CUSHING uses the SQQ-89 sonar system--the most advanced ASW equipment in existence--to accomplish this complex and demanding task.  The ship is equipped with a sophisticated sonar, the AN/SQS-53C, that is directly integrated with a third generation digital computer system, the Naval Tactical Data System (NTDS).  In addition to its bow mounted sonar, CUSHING has a passive towed array sonar system.  CUSHING's ASW suite includes two triple barreled torpedo tubes and carries two Light Airborne Multipurpose System (LAMPS) MK III ASW helicopters.  LAMPS is a computer integrated ship/helicopter system, whose primary missions are ASW (to detect, localize and attack subsurface contacts) and Anti-Ship surveillance and targeting (to detect and track surface contacts and provide targeting information for surface-to-surface missiles).  The integrated combat system provides CUSHING with an enhanced target information processing capability and an extremely fast reaction time in response to a wide variety of threats.<br>
CUSHING also boasts the Tomahawk Weapons Control System, the MK 41 Vertical Launching System, two  5 inch/54 caliber fully automatic gun mounts (controlled by the digital Mk 86 Gun Fire Control System), the Harpoon surface-to-surface missile system, and the NATO Sea Sparrow missile system, which provides defense against air targets.  Also integrated with NTDS, those weapon systems allow CUSHING to excel in its other primary mission area of Strike Warfare, Naval Gunfire Support (NGFS), Anti-Surface Warfare (ASUW) and Anti-Air Warfare (AAW).  CUSHING's Close-In Weapons System (CIWS) provides the ship with the most up to date anti-cruise missile defense available.<br>

<pre><strong>Ship's Characteristics:</strong>
Length....................................563 ft 4 in
Beam......................................55 ft
Displacement..............................8,300 tons
Speed.....................................30 KNOTS

<strong>Armament</strong>
Two Five-Inch 54 CAL. MK45 Gun Mounts
Tomahawk Missile System
NATO Sea Sparrow Missile System
Harpoon Missile System
Six MK 32 Torpedo Tubes
Two 20MM Close-in Weapons System (CWIS) Mounts

<strong>AIRCRAFT</strong>
Two SH-60B LAMPS MKIII Helicopters

<strong>PROPULSION</strong>
Four General Electric LM-2500 Gas Turbine Engines
     (TOTAL-80,000 SHAFT HORSEPOWER)

<strong>Compliment</strong>
Officers...................................25
Enlisted...................................330

<strong>CUSHING Milestones</strong>
Keel Laid..................................2 February 1977
Christened.................................29 July 1978
Commissioned...............................20 October 1979
Most Recent Overhaul.......................27 September 13-21 August 1995
<br>
</pre>
<br>
