<h1>RIMPAC 96<BR>Multi-National Force:<BR><br>Tactical Electronic Warfare Squadron 135 (VAQ-135)</h1>
<br><br><br>
<title>Tactical Electronic Warfare Squadron 135 (VAQ-135)</title>
<hr>
<h2><br>Tactical Electronic Warfare Squadron 135 (VAQ-135) Black Ravens</h2>
<pre>
Homeport................................Naval Air Station,
                                        Whidbey Island, Washington
Commanding Officer......................Commander Preston C. Pinson, USN

<strong>Squadron manning</strong>
Officers................................27
Chiefs..................................10
Enlisted................................154
Aircraft................................GRUMMAN EA-6B Prowler
Engines.................................2 - PRATT & WHITNEY J52 P-408a
Thrust..................................10,400lbs per Engine
Wing span...............................53ft
Length..................................60ft
Dry weight..............................33,000lbs
Combat load.............................56,000lbs
</pre>
<a href="vaq135px.htm"><img src="vaq135.gif" alt="VAQ-135 EA-6B aircraft" align="left" height=320 width=400></a>
<strong>Mission</strong><br>
The main mission of VAQ-135 is Electronic Attack in order to suppress the enemy's air defense systems.  This includes listening for radar emissions, jamming radar, and the employment of anti-radiation missiles.  The EA-6B uses these tools in order to provide the airwing with a sanctury which will be used to make a succesful strike and minimize friendly aircraft losses.
<br>
<br>
<h5>Source - CVW-11</h5><br>
