<br><br>
<h1>RIMPAC 96<BR>Multi-National Force:<BR>Helicopter Anti-Submarine Squadron Six (HS-6)</h1>
<title>Helicopter Anti-Submarine Squadron Six (HS-6)</title>
<hr>
<h2>Helicopter Anti-Submarine Squadron Six (HS-6) Indians</h2>
<pre>
Homeport.....................Naval Air Station North Island, San Diego, CA
Commanding Officer...........Commander John S. Rosa, USN

<strong>Squadron Manning:</strong>
Officers.....................28
Chiefs.......................14
Junior Enlisted..............156
</pre>
<strong>Aircraft</strong><br>
HH-60H and SH-60F helicopters.  They are configured with a single main rotor, twin engines, a 20 degree tractor-type canted tail rotor, a controllable stabilator, conventional fixed landing gear, an external cargo hook, a rescue hoist, and weapons pylons for carrying and launching external stores.<br>

<dl><strong>Primary Mission</strong>
<dt>HH-60H: <dd>Combat search and rescue and naval special warfare support.
<dt>SH-60F: <dd>Anti-submarine warfare(ASW) defense of CV inner zone, which includes the detection, classification, and destruction of hostile submarines.  Secondary missions are combat search and rescue (CSAR), and naval special warfare support.
</dl>
<a href="hs6pic.htm"><img src="hs6.gif" alt="HS-6 Helicopter" align="left" height=320 width=400></a>
<strong>Secondary Missions</strong><br>
Logistic support, vertical replinishment (VERTREP), anti-surface warfare (ASUW) and medical evacuation (MEDEVAC).
<br>
<h5>Source - CVW-11</h5><br>
