<h1>RIMPAC 96<BR>Multi-National Force:<BR>USS CLEVELAND<br>(LPD 7)</h1>
<br><br><br>
<title>USS CLEVELAND (LPD 7)</title>
<hr>
<img src="lpd7.gif" alt= "" align=right align=middle height=250 width=400>
<h2>USS CLEVELAND<br>(LPD 7)</h2>
Since commissioning in 1967, USS CLEVELAND (LPD 7) has sailed hundreds of thousands of miles and participated in events.  The ship, a Vietnam, Operation Desert Shield and Desert Storm veteran, has also worked to help clean up oil spills off Prince William Sound, Alaska, and has assisted in anti-drug law enforcement operations off the coast of South America.<br>
USS CLEVELAND, as an Amphibious Landing Dock Ship, brings Marines to the battlefield, deploying troops via landing craft from the ship's well deck.<br>
<pre>
<strong>Ship's Characteristics</strong>
Length............................................570 feet
Propulsion..Two 600-lb Steam Turbine Engines (1 per shaft)
Beam..............................................105 feet
Draft..............................................23 feet
Displacement...................................16,500 tons
Speed..............................................21 knots

<strong>Launched:</strong>       May 7, 1967
<strong>Commissioned:</strong>   April 21, 1967
<strong>Homeport:</strong>       San Diego, CA.

<strong>Normal Compliment:</strong>      420 Officers and Enlisted
<strong>Deployed Compliment:</strong>  1,300 (Flag-75, USMC Troops-825)
</pre>
<br>
<h5>Source: - U.S. THIRD FLEET</h5><br>
