<br><h1>RIMPAC 96<BR>Multi-National Force:<br>Chilean Navy frigate<br>ALMIRANTE LYNCH<br>(PFG 07)</h1>
<title>CS ALMIRANTE LYNCH (PFG 07)</title>
<hr>
<img src="r96bot13.gif" alt= "" align=right align=middle height=223 width=400>
<h2>CS ALMIRANTE LYNCH<br>(PFG 07)</h2>

<h3>Historical Description</h3>
The PFG "ALMIRANTE LYNCH" is a "LEANDER" Class, general purpose frigate, build at Yarrow Shipbuilders LTD., SCOTSFON, SCOTLAND.  Launched December 6th, 1972 and Commissioned May 25th 1974.  She later underwent an adjustment and trial period.<br>
She sailed from Portland on January  9th, 1975, arriving at the First Chilean Port of Punta Arenas on February 6th.  On February 14th, 1975 she joined the squadron in Valparaiso.<br>
Her name honors the memory of Vice Admiral Patricio Lynch Solo De Zaldivar, one of the most distinguished men in the Chilean Naval and Military History.<br>
He Served in  the Royal Navy between 1839 and 1847, attaining the ran of Lieutenant, his distinguished participation in the English/Chinese war gained him a special Queen Victory Medal.<br>
Upon return to the Chilean Navy, he took part in the actions of the war against Spain and later, in the pacific war against Peru and Bolivia, in this war, he assumed command of the Transport Group and them, as the political and military Chief of Tarapaca when IQUIQUE was recovered by the Chilean forces.<br>
In 1881, he become Commander in Chief of the Occupation forces in Lima, Peru, executing the  political and Military control with an uncommon skill.  During his administration, he planned and personally directed expeditions to the Peruvian interior.<br>
After the war, he was appointed as a special messenger and Plenipotenciary Minster of the Chilean Republic to the Spanish Government.  He died on May 13th., 1886.<br>
The PFG "LYNCH" is the third ship of the Chilean Navy to bear this name.  The first was a torpedo boat chaser built in Birhenhead in 1888;  and the second, a fleet destroyer built cowes in 1991.<br>

<pre>
<strong>Basic Statistical Data</strong>

Length:..............................113 Meters
Width................................12 Meters
Maximum Speed........................28 Knots

<strong>Propulsion</strong>
Two propeller powered by two steam turbine providing
30,000 Shaft horsepower

<strong>Armament</strong>
<ul>
<li>Missile SU/SU Exocet MM40
<li>Missile SU/A Seacat
<li>Double Propose 4,5" Turret
<li>Torpedo MK 44
<li>Multipurpose Helicopter SH-32 Cougar
</ul>
<strong>Crew</strong>
Officer...............................22
Enlisted Men..........................245
</pre>
<br>
<h5>Source - Chilean Navy</h5><br>
