<h1>Senator McCain Arriving at the<br>
CINCPACFLT Change of Command Ceremony</h1>
<title>Senator McCain Arriving at the Ceremony</title>
<hr><br>
<img src="mccainar.gif" alt="Senator McCain Arriving at the Ceremony" align="left" height=278 width=400>
<strong>(November 7, 1996)</strong> -- "As Commander in Chief of the U.S. Pacific Fleet, Adm. Zlatoper made tough decisions about long ship deployments from homeports and loved ones, but most importantly, in his 
determination to improve the quality of life of Navy personnel, he gave a much louder voice to the Sailors in Navy decisions about issues affecting their well-being," said Senator John McCain about long-time friend and colleague Admiral R. J. Zlatoper at the CINCPACFLT change of command ceremony.  "The men and women he commanded responded to his superb leadership by performing superbly themselves in places like the Taiwan Straits, the Korean Peninsula and the skies over Iraq."  Admiral Archie Clemins relieved Zlatoper as the Pacific Fleet Commander in Chief. (Official U.S. Navy Photo by JO1 Robert Benson)<br><br>
