<DOCNO>WT22-B15-185</DOCNO>
<DOCOLDNO>IA023-000251-B027-127</DOCOLDNO>
<DOCHDR>
http://www.cpf.navy.mil:80/cg59bio.htm 199.124.15.66 19970108120706 text/html 3169
HTTP/1.0 200 OK
Date: Wed, 08 Jan 1997 12:19:12 GMT
Server: Microsoft-Internet-Information-Server/1.0
Content-Type: text/html
</DOCHDR>
<!--Maintained by JOC(SW) C.A. McIntire-->
<!--Code N00pa2b-->
<!--phone: (808) 471-3769-->
<!--e-mail: u00pa2b@cpf-emh.cpf.navy.mil-->
<html>

<title>CO, USS ()</title>

<body background="chalk.jpg">
<img src="cg59co.gif" alt=""ALIGN= RIGHT ALIGN=MIDDLE width=280 height=356></h1>
<h1>Captain<br>
Dallas G. Wilfong, III, USN</h1>
<h2>Commanding Officer,<br>
USS PRINCETON<br>(CG 59)</h2>
Captain Dallas G. Wilfong, III is a native of Charlottesville, Virginia.  He graduated from the University of Virginia in June 1972, with a Bachelor of Science Degree in Commerce and regular commission through the Navy Reserve Officer Training Corps.<br>
Captain Wilfong's initial sea duty assignment was to USS DALE (DLG 19) where he served as Combat Information Center Officer.  Upon completion of the Destroyer Department Head Course in February 1979, Captain Wilfong's was assigned as Operations Officer in USS SOMERS (DDG 34).  He has subsequently served at sea as Combat Systems Officer in USS HALSEY (CG 23), Combat System Officer for Cruiser Destroyer Group FIVE, Executive Officer in USS CALLAGHAN,(DDG 994), and Commanding Officer of USS ELLIOT (DD 967).  During Captain Wilfong's tour USS ELLIOT deployed to the Indian Ocean in support of Operation Desert Storm and won the Battle Efficiency Competition Award for Destroyer Squadron Thirteen.<br>
Captain Wilfong's first shore tour was as a Navigation Instructor at United States Naval Academy.  He attended George Washington University where he received a Master of Science Degree in Information systems.  Before reporting to USS ELLIOT (DDG 967), Captain Wilfong was assigned to the Office of the Chief of Naval Operations as Program Coordinator for the ARLEIGH BURKE (DDG 51) and AEGIS Shipbuilding Programs, and subsequently as a financial analyst in the Office of Program Appraisal.  He graduated from the National War College at Washington, DC in June 1990.  Captain Wilfong served on the staff of the Director, Surface Warfare Division from August 1992 to September 1994 as Head of the Area/Theater Ballistic Missile Defense and AEGIS Branch; and subsequently as the Deputy Director for Theater Air Defense.<br>
Captain Wilfong's personal awards and decorations include the Legion of Merit, Meritorious Service Medal with two Gold Stars, and the Navy Commendation Medal with two Gold Stars.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
