<html>

<title>CO, Pacific Missile Range Facility</title>

<body background="chalk.jpg">
<img src="pmrfco.gif" align="right" height=352 width=280><h1>Thomas L. Daniels<br>
Captain, USN</h1>
<h2>Commanding Officer,<br>
Pacific Missile Range Facility<br>
Barking Sands</h2>
Captain Tom Daniels, the son of John and Katherine Daniels, grew up in Ripley, Tennessee.  He attended the University of Mississippi School Of Engineering on a full Naval Reserve Officers Training Corps scholarship and was commissioned on 25 January 1971.  He was designated a Naval Flight Officer in November 1971.<br>
Captain Daniels' first operational assignment was as a Bombardier/Navigator in A-6's with VA-115 flying combat missions Into Vietnam.  This tour also was MIDWAY's initial home port change to Yokosuka, Japan.  Captain Daniels' second tour began In March 1975 at the Naval Postgraduate School where he received a Masters of Science degree In Operations Research. He next served as the Assistant Strike Operations Officer onboard USS RANGER until 1979.<br>
After this WESTPAC tour, Captain Daniels served at the Naval Weapons 
Center in China Lake, California as the Deputy Director of the A-6 Weapon System Support Activity.  His next tour took Captain Daniels to the east coast with VA-75.  In addition to his department head tour as Maintenance Officer, Captain Daniels served as Officer in Charge of a special three month detachment to augment VA-65 aboard USS EISENHOWER during the height of the Eastern Mediterranean tensions.<br>
The Pentagon was Captain Daniels' duty station from September 1985 - November 1988.  Here he served In OP-815 as an analyst specializing In the Navy's future attack aircraft and weapons systems.  The second portion of this split tour was in OF-741 where be worked on Strike Warfare Appraisals and Master Plans.<br>
Captain Daniels reported to Training Squadron TEN In February 1989 where he served as Commanding Officer.  At the end of this tour, his squadron was awarded the Vice Admiral Goldthwaite Award as the best of twenty-two commands in CNATRA as well as receiving the Meritorious Unit Commendation for outstanding performance.  Following the Program Management Course at tile Defense Systems Management College in December 1991, Captain Daniels reported to Program Manager Conventional Strike Weapons (PMA-201) where he served as the Deputy Program Manager for the ACAT 1D joint Standoff Weapon (JSOW Program.  In July 1993, he reported as the Executive Assistant to the Commander, Naval Air Warfare Center.  On 30 June 1994, Captain Daniels assumed command at his present duty station, Pacific Missile Range Facility, Barking Sands, Hawaii.<br>
Among Captain Daniels' awards are the Distinguished Flying Cross,
Meritorious Service Medals, one individual Air Medal, five
Strike/Flight Air Medals and tile Navy Commendation Medal.<br>
Captain Daniels is married to the former Martha Elaine Wiggins of
Pensacola, Florida.<br>
<br>
<br>
