<html>
<head>
<title>
Battle Force SEVENTH Fleet  - Chief of Staff
</title>
</head>
<body>
<center><img src="cos.jpg"></a><br>
<h2>CAPT Charles B. Beckman</h2><br>
<h2>Chief of Staff<br>
Battle Force SEVENTH Fleet<br>
Surface Combatant Force SEVENTH Fleet<br>
Carrier Strike Force SEVENTH Fleet<br>
Carrier Group FIVE</h2><br>


</center>
<p>Captain Charles B. Beckman, a native of Centralia, Missouri, graduated from the United States Naval Academy in June 1970.    He subsequently attended nuclear power training at Bainbridge, Maryland, and Windsor, Connecticut. </p>

<p>In January 1972, following the completion of Naval Submarine School in New London, Connecticut, he reported to USS POGY (SSN 647) where he served as Reactor Controls Officer and Sonar Officer.  After attending Submarine Officer Advanced Course at Submarine School, Captain Beckman reported to USS ABRAHAM LINCOLN (SSBN 602) (Gold) where he served as Communicator and Main Propulsion Assistant. </p>

<p>In July 1976, he reported to the staff of Commander, Submarine Squadron SIXTEEN in Rota, Spain as the Assistant Readiness and Training Officer.  In January 1978, he assumed duty as Engineering Officer of USS POLLACK (SSN 603) until July 1981. </p>

	Captain Beckman reported to USS PUFFER (SSN 652) as Executive Officer in November 1981.  In September 1984, he assumed duty in the Office of the Chief of Naval Operations as SSN Assistant to the Director, Antisubmarine Warfare Division (OP-951).  In April 1987, he assumed command of USS LOUISVILLE (SSN 724), taking the ship through Post Shakedown Availability, a change of homeport to San Diego, California, and a Western Pacific deployment. </p>

<p>In May 1990, Captain Beckman reported to the staff of commander, SEVENTH Fleet in Yokosuka, Japan.  During Operations DESERT STORM and DESERT SHIELD he served as Warfare Officer, command and Control Officer, and Battle Watch Captain on the staff of Commander U.S. Naval Forces Central Command.  He later became the Command and Control, Communications, Computers and Intelligence Officer for SEVENTH Fleet Staff. </p>

<p>Captain Beckman reported to USS NEBRASKA (SSBN 739) in November 1992, as the Gold Crew Commanding Officer.  Under his command, the ship completed shakedown operations, strategic missile loadout, and the first deterrent patrol.  Following command, he attended executive education at Harvard Business School's Advanced Management Program. </p>

<p>In February 1995, Captain Beckman assumed duties as Chief of Staff, Commander, Battle Force SEVENTH Fleet/Commander Surface Combatant Force SEVENTH Fleet/Commander Carrier Strike Force SEVENTH Fleet and Commander Carrier Group FIVE. </p>

<p>Captain Beckman's decorations include the Legion of Merit, Meritorious Service Medal (five), Navy Commendation Medal, Navy Achievement Medal (two awards), and various unit and campaign awards. </p>

<p>Captain Beckman is married to Lieutenant Margaret Marshall, who is the Director, Counseling and Assistance Center, Yokosuka, Japan.  His daughter, Tish, lives in Los Angeles, California. </p>

</body>
