<html>
<body background="chalk.jpg">
<img src="rimpac4.gif"  alt= ""align=left align=middle height=191 width=250>
<title>History of PATWINGSPAC</title>
<h1>History of<br>
Commander, Patrol Wings,<br>
U.S. Pacific Fleet</h1>
<hr>
The Navy's Pacific land-based anti-submarine warfare organization was commissioned on 1 January 1964 at Naval Air Station, Moffett Field, California as Commander Fleet Air Wings pacific to provide administrative command training of all patrol squadrons in the Pacific theater.<br>
On 1 July 1965, the command received an additional hat as Commander Fleet Air Moffett with responsibility for the overall operation of Naval Air Station, Moffett Field and operational control of the squadrons home-based at Moffett.  In September 1967, Commander Patrol Force Pacific was commissioned with responsibility for 13 patrol squadrons and two patrol wings.<br>
On 1 July 1973, the responsibilities of Commander Fleet Air Wings pacific, commander Fleet Air Moffett and Commander Patrol Force Pacific were combined into one new designation...Commander, patrol Wings, U.S. Pacific Fleet.<br>
Commander, Patrol Wings, U.S. Pacific Fleet is responsible for one Naval Air Station, one Naval air Facility, two Patrol Wing Staffs, one Strategic Communications Wing Staff, six patrol squadrons, one fleet air reconnaissance squadron, two strategic communication squadrons, one special projects unit, the Pacific Fleet Missile Range at Barking Sands, and five Tactical Support Centers spread throughout the Pacific and Indian Ocean regions.<br>
The command moved from Naval Air Station, Moffett Field to Naval Air Station, Barbers Point on 1 July 1993.<br>
<br><br>
<center>-USN-</center>
<br>
<br>
