<br><br><br>
<h1>RIMPAC 96<BR>Cruiser Destroyer Group FIVE</h1>
<br><br><br><br>
<title>Cruiser Destroyer Group FIVE</title>
<hr>
<h2>Cruiser Destroyer Group FIVE</h2>
Cruiser-Destroyer Group FIVE's mission is to pursue national objectives by planning for and exercising operational and tactical command of air,
surface and subsurface forces at sea, in a multi-threat environment.<br>
Commander, Cruiser-Destroyer Group FIVE is directly responsible to Commander, Naval Surface Forces, U.S. Pacific Fleet for the administration and readiness of assigned ships within the group administrative organization.  When serving as Task Force Commander, The Commander is also responsible to the Commander, Naval Air Forces, U. S. Pacific Fleet for certain administrative functions concerning the aircraft carrier and carrier air wing.  In addition, he serves as a subordinate Operational Commander to Commander Third Fleet and Commander Seventh Fleet when assigned in the Eastern Pacific and Western Pacific, respectively.  The Commander Cruiser-Destroyer Group FIVE staff is comprised of 25 officers and 33 enlisted personnel.<br>
The following units are permanently assigned to Cruiser-Destroyer Group FIVE.
<br>
<ul>
<li>USS KITTY HAWK (CV-63)
<li>USS ANTIETAM (CG-54)
<li>USS COWPENS (CG-63)
<li>DESTROYER SQUADRON 31
<li>CARRIER AIR WING 11
<li>VF-213
<li>VFA-97
<li>VFA-22
<li>VFA-94
<li>VAQ-135
<li>VS-29
<li>VAW-117
<li>VQ-5
<li>HS-6
</ul>
<br>
<h5>Source: - Cruiser Destroyer Group FIVE</h5><br>
