<html>

<title>CO, USS CUSHING (DD-895)</title>
<body background="chalk.jpg">
<h1>Patrick D. Myers<br>
Commander, USN</h1>
<h2>Commanding Officer,<br>
USS CUSHING (DD-985)</h2>
Commander Myers was born December 28, 1954 in Hillsboro, Oregon to Edward and Frances Myers.  He graduated from Hillsboro High School in June 1973, then continued his education at the University of Notre Dame.  He earned a Bachelor of Science Degree in Biology and received his commission in May 1977.  Commander Myers subsequently earned a Master of Science Degree in Operations Research from the Naval Postgraduate School in 1985.<br>
Commander Myers initial sea duty assignment was as the Minesweeping and Executive Officer on board USS IMPLICIT (MSO 455) homeported in Tacoma, Washington.  Commander Myers remained on sea duty, serving as the Weapons Systems Officer on board USS JOUETT (CG 29) homeported in Long Beach then San Diego, California.  Upon completion of Naval Postgraduate School, he served as Combat Systems Officer on board USS LEFTWICH (DD 984) homeported in Pearl Harbor, Hawaii.  Commander Myers first significant shore duty assignment was as a Cost Analyst on the Office of the Secretary of  Defense staff at the Pentagon.  He returned to sea duty as Executive Officer on board USS ELLIOT (DD 967) homeported in San Diego, California.  He continued on sea duty as Chief Staff Officer for Commander Destroyer Squadron Twenty-one also in San Diego.  Commander Myers' most recent assignment was       at the Pentagon as a Requirements Analyst for the Expeditionary Warfare Division.<br>
Commander Myers' personal awards include the Defense Meritorious Service Medal, Meritorious Service Medal, Navy Commendation Medal (3), and the Navy Achievement Medal (3).<br>
Commander Myers and his wife Nancy (Piontkowski), also a native of Hillsboro, Oregon were married in January 1978.  They have three sons, Dominic (age 13), Sean (age 11), and Aaron (age 9).<br>
<br>
<br>
