<html>
<head>
<title>
USS INDEPENDENCE - VQ-5
</title>
</head>
<body>
<center>
<img src="vq5lg.gif"></a> <img src="vq5px.jpg"></a><br>
<h2> Fleet Air Reconnaissance Squadron FIVE Detachment FIVE</h2><br>
</center>

<p>
	VQ-5 Det 5 is a permanently assigned 2-plane detachment to Carrier Air Wing Five(CVW-5) which deploys onboard USS INDEPENDENCE. The detachment is assigned to NAF Misawa, Japan when not deployed at sea. The detachment flies the ES-3A Shadow which provides indications and warnings for the Battle Group commander.  Normally assigned to AQ, the Command and Control Warfare commander, for tasking and mission assignment, the detachment also flies strike support missions, war at sea missions, and OTHT missions in support of other warfare commanders. The aircraft is also configured as an airborne refueling platform which performs emergency/mission tanking when required. <br><br>
	The parent squadron for the detachment is VQ-5, which is homeported in NAS North Island, CA. The squadron was established at NAS Agana, Guam in 1991. The squadron was moved to NAS North Island in 1994 in order to support the fleet more effectively.  In response to 7th Fleet directive, VQ-5 Det 5 was established in 1994 to provide support for 7th Fleet assets.  VQ-5 Det Five has participated in the following deployments and operations: Operation  Southern Watch (2 deployments), AnnualEx,  Foal Eagle, Vigilant Sentinel, Cobra Gold, Valiant Usher, Cope North, Team Spirit,  RIMPAC (2 deployments) and various contingency operations. The detachment is the only carrier borne VQ detachment which routinely conducts joint/multinational training on a regular basis. The squadron is currently commanded by CDR R. W. Radloff . The current detachment Officer in Charge is LCDR Dan "Club" Moore. <br><br>

<p>
