<!--Maintained by JOC(SW) C.A. McIntire-->
<!--Code N00pa2b-->
<!--phone: (808) 471-3769-->
<!--e-mail: u00pa2b@cpf-emh.cpf.navy.mil-->
<html>
<title>CO, USS ESSEX (LHD 2)</title>
<body background="chalk.jpg">
<IMG SRC="lhd2seal.gif" alt= ""align=right align=middle height=341 width=280></hi>
<h1>Captain<br>
Thomas F. Radich, USN</h1>
<h2>Commanding Officer,<br>
USS ESSEX (LHD 2)</h2>
Captain Thomas Francis Radich graduated from the United States Naval Academy in Annapolis, Maryland, and was commissioned on June  9, 1971.  Captain Radich reported July 1971 for his initial seatour o USS HERMATAGE (LSD 34) as 1st Division Officer and then Navigator.  In September 1974, he returned to the Naval Academy as a Seamanship and Navigation Instructor.<br>
Concurrently, he earned a Master of Science Degree from George Washington University, graduating in February 1977.  After completing Department head School in August 1978, he returned to sea in September 1978 serving consecutive Department Head tours as Operations Officer in USS GRAY (FF 1054) and then as First Lieutenant in USS BRISTOL COUNTY (LST 1198).<br>
In January 1983, CAPT Radich reported as Shipboard Management Department Head at Surface Warfare Officer School in Coronado, California.  He was subsequently assigned as Executive Officer in USS ALAMO (LSD 33) in March 1985. He was ordered to Washington, D.C. in January 1987 as the Amphibious Plans and programs Officer for tile Assistant Chief of Naval Operations (Surface Warfare)(OP013).<br>
Captain Radich then commanded the USS FORT FISHER (LSD 40) from December 1989 to January 1992.  During his command tour, FORT FISHER deployed to the Western Pacific and participated in numerous operations in the Eastern Pacific including  a highly successful Counter narcotics operation in South America.  FORT FISHER was subsequently awarded the coveted Battle Efficiency "E" and the Joint Meritorious Unit Award.<br>
In February 1992, Captain Raclich reported to the Bureau of Naval Personnel as Deputy Director, Surface Officer Distributions Division (Pers 41B).  In August 1994, he was assigned as a student at the National War College and was awarded a Master of Science in National Security Policy in June 1995.<br>
Captain Radich relieved as Commanding Officer, USS ESSEX (LHD 2) on October 20, 1995.<br>
Captain Radich's decorations include three Meritorious Service Medals the Navy Commendation Medal and the Navy Achievement Medal.<br>
Captain Radich is the son of Mr. and Mrs. R. Leo Radich of Beach Haven Terrace, New Jersey.  He is married to the former Judy Jeanette Jones of Annapolis, Maryland.  They have two sons, Thomas, age 16, and Christopher, age 12.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
