<html>
<body background="chalk.jpg">
<img src="rimpac3.gif" alt= "" align=left align=middle height=145 width=190>
<img src="sealusmc.gif" alt= "" align=right align=middle height=145 width=151>
<br><center><h1>RIMPAC 96<BR>Multi-National Force:<br><br>11th Marine Expeditionary Unit</center></h1>
<hr>
<h1>Lieutenant Colonel Stuart R. McMeans</h1>
<h2>Commanding Officer
Marine Medium Helicopter Squadron - 166 (Rein)</h2>
Lieutenant Colonel Stuart R. McMeans was born in Bovina, Texas and attended Texas Tech University, graduating with a BBA in Accounting.  He entered the Marine Corps through Officer Candidate School June 13, 1976.<br>
Upon completion of The Basic School, LtCol. McMeans was assigned to Pensacola, Florida for flight training and was designated a Naval Aviator in August 1978.  After transitioning to the CH-46 at HMT-301, 3rd Marine Aircraft Wing, he was assigned to HMM-265 at Marine Corps Air Station Kaneohe Bay, Hawaii from March 1979 to February 1982.  During this tour he served in the Administration and Maintenance sections and participated in two Western Pacific deployments.  He finished his Hawaii tour as the Air Officer for the First Marine Brigade.<br>
In February 1982, LtCol. McMeans was transferred to Naval Air Station Corpus Christi, Texas for duty as a Flight Instructor in VT-27.  He instructed in the T-28 Trojan and served as a Flight Leader and Assistant Operations Officer.  In January 1985, he was transferred to 2nd Air Naval Gunfire Liaison Company at Camp Lejeune, North Carolina.  In November 1985, he deployed as the first  ANGLICO Detachment Officer-in-Charge to take a Det. with a Marine Amphibious Unit (Special Operations Capable).  During this deployment, he participated in operations against Libya with the Sixth Fleet.<br>
In July 1986, he transferred to MCAS New River, North Carolina where he completed refresher training in the CH-46 at HMT-204 before transferring to HMM-365.  During this tour he completed two Mediterranean deployments and served as the Director of Safety and Standardization, Administrative Officer, and Operations Officer.  In September 1990, LtCol. McMeans reported to HMX-1 at Quantico, Virginia and served as the Director of Operational Test and Evaluation, Operations Officer, and as a Presidential Command Pilot.<br>
LtCol. McMeans reported to Marine Aircraft Group-16 in October 1994 and was transferred to HMM-166 in December 1994 as the Executive Officer.  He assumed command May 11, 1995.<br>
His personal decorations include the Meritorious Service Medal, Air Medal w/Gold Numeral One, and the Navy Achievement medal.<br>
He is married to the former Linda Hopwood of Scottsburg, Indiana.  She is a Lieutenant Commander in the U.S. Navy. <br>
<hr>
<h5>Source - 11th MEU</h5><br>
