<hr>
<h1>Squad Automatic Weapon</h1>
The M-249 SAW is an individually portable, gas-operated, magazine or disintegrating metallic link-belt fed, light machine gun with a quick change barrel feature that replaced the M-16 as the automatic rifle in the fire team, forming the basis of firepower for the fire team.<br>
The gunner has the option of using the linked ammunition from a pre-loaded 200-round plastic box magazine or the 30-round M-16 magazine.  The gunner’s basic load is 600 rounds of linked ammunition.<br>
The SAW increases the firepower of Marine infantry units, with a capability of engaging point targets as far as 800 meters, firing the improved, NATO standard 5.56mm cartridge.<br>

<h3>Specifications</h3>
<pre>
Range....................................1,000 meters (for an area target)

Rates of fire
Cyclic...................................725 rounds per minute
Sustained................................85  rounds per minute

Weight...................................15.16 pounds
Length...................................40.87 inches
Magazine capacity........................30-round M16 magazine
                                         200-round box magazine
Caliber..................................5.56mm
</pre>

