<br><center><h1>RIMPAC 96<BR>Multi-National Force:<br><br>11th Marine Expeditionary Unit</center></h1>
<hr>
<h1>M-60E3 Machine Gun</h1>
The M-60E3 machine gun is a 7.62 mm, lightweight, air-cooled, disintegrating metallic link-belt fed, portable or tripod mounted machine gun designed for ground operations.  It is gas operated with fixed head space and timing which permits rapid changing of barrels.<br>
Slightly different from its "parent," the M-60, it has a receiver- attached bipod which easily deploys for stability.  It has an ambidextrous safety mechanism, universal sling attachments, a carrying handle on the barrel, and a simplified gas system.<br>
The M60-E3 was fielded with the intention to reduce the load carried by the gunner.  However, the reduction in weight resulted in firing limitations and a loss of reliability.<br>
Consequently, the Marine Corps began replacing this  weapon with the M-240G during Fiscal Year 1995.  The 11th MEU has a handful in its inventory.<br>

<h3>Specifications</h3>
<pre>
Maximum effective range.........................1,000 meters
                                                (for an area target)
Maximum range...................................2.3 miles

Rates of fire
Cyclic..........................................550 rounds per minute
Rapid...........................................100 rounds per minute *
Sustained.......................................100 rounds per minute *
* (with barrel changes at each 100 rounds)
	
Weight..........................................18.75 pounds
Length..........................................42.4 inches
Caliber.........................................7.62mm
</pre>
<hr>
