<hr>
<h1>M-240G Machine Gun</h1>
The M-240G Machine Gun is the ground version of the M-240 which is mounted on tanks and light armored vehicles.  It is a medium machine gun, 7.62 (.30 caliber) fired from ground position.  The M-240G is modified for ground use by installation of a buttstock and bipod, front and rear sights and a flash suppressor.<br>
The rate of fire for the M-240G may be controlled by three different regulator settings for single rounds, short bursts or sustained fire.<br>
The durability of the M-240G results in superior reliability and maintainability over the M-60 machine gun, currently being replaced by the M-240G.<br>

<h3>Specifications </h3>
<pre>
Range
Maximum......................................2.31 miles
Max Effective................................1.1 miles

Rates of Fire
Cyclic.......................................65-950 rounds per min.
Rapid........................................200 rounds per min.
Sustained....................................100 rounds per min.

Length.......................................47.5 inches
Weight.......................................12 pounds
Bore Diameter................................7.62mm
</pre>
<hr>
<h5>Source - 11th MEU</h5><br>
