<img src="sealusmc.gif" alt= "" align=right align=middle height=145 width=151>
<br><center><h1>RIMPAC 96<BR>Multi-National Force:<br><br>11th Marine Expeditionary Unit</center></h1>
<hr>
<h1>Mortars</h1>
<h2>60mm Mortar</h2>
The M-224 60mm Lightweight Mortar is a smooth bore, muzzle loading, high angle-of-fire weapon.<br>
The cannon assembly is composed of the barrel, combination base cap, and firing mechanism.  The mount consists of a bipod and a base plate which is provided with screw type elevating and traversing mechanisms. The M-64 Sight Unit is attached to the bipod mount.  An additional short range sight is attached  to the base of the cannon tube for firing the mortar on the move and during assaults.<br>

Specifications
<pre>
Range......................................2.17 miles

Rates of fire
Maximum....................................30 rounds per minute
Sustained..................................20 rounds per minute

Weight.....................................46.5 pounds
Length.....................................40 inches
</pre>
<hr>
<h2>81mm Mortar</h2>
The M-252 81mm Medium Extended Range Mortar is a crew-served, medium-weight mortar which is highly accurate and provides for a greater range (4,500 meters to 5,650 meters) and lethality than the previous 81mm mortar.<br>
The cannon has a crew-removable breech plug and firing pin.  The muzzle end has a short tapered lead-in which acts as a blast attenuator device.  
This mortar also uses the standard M-64 mortar sight of the 60mm mortar, M-224.<br>

Specifications
<pre>
Range......................................3.51  miles

Rates of fire
Maximum....................................33 rounds per minute
Sustained..................................16 rounds per minute

Weight
Assembly...................................35 pounds
Bipod......................................26 pounds
Baseplate..................................25.5 pounds
Sight Unit.................................2.5 pounds
                                    Total  89 pounds	

Length	
Bore.......................................50.3 inches
Mortar.....................................56 inches
</pre>
<hr>
<h5>Source - 11th MEU</h5><br>
