<hr>
<h1>At-4 Anti-Tank Weapon</h1>
The AT-4 antitank weapon is a lightweight, expandable, self-contained rocket launcher that fires a single rocket.  It is designed to allow gunners to destroy such targets as enemy tanks and armored vehicles.<br>
It consists of an 84mm cone-shaped warhead designed to penetrate armor plate.  Both the warhead and its rocket motor are housed in an expendable, reinforced, fiberglass launch tube.  It is fired by an individual Marine from the shoulder position.<br>

<h3>Specifications </h3>
<pre>
Range.............................................984.3 feet
Speed.............................................Supersonic in flight
Time of Flight(to 250 meters).....................Less than 1 second
Penetration.......................................400mm of rolled
                                                  homogenous armor
Ammunition........................................Rocket w/shaped charge
                                                  warhead
Muzzle Velocity...................................950 feet per second
Length............................................40 inches
Weight............................................14.75 pounds
Bore diameter.....................................84mm
Manufacturer......................................FFV Ordnance
Unit Replacement Cost.............................$1,028
</pre>
