<br><center><h1>RIMPAC 96<BR>Multi-National Force:<br><br>11th Marine Expeditionary Unit</center></h1>
<hr>
<h1>SMAW Rocket Launcher</h1>
The Shoulder-Launched Multipurpose Assault Weapon is a portable antiarmor rocket launcher.  It is used to destroy bunkers and other fortifications during assault operations as well as other designated targets with the High Explosive Dual Purpose rocket and to destroy main battle tanks with the High Explosive Antiarmor rocket.<br>
The SMAW is an 83mm man-portable weapon system consisting of a Launcher, an encased HEDP rocket, an encased HEAA rocket, and a spotting rifle cartridge.
The launcher consists of a fiberglass launch tube, a 9mm spotting rifle, an electro-mechanical firing mechanism, open battle sights and a mount for night sights The HEDP rocket is effective against bunkers, masonry and concrete walls, and light armor.  The HEAA rocket is effective against current tanks without additional armor.<br>
The 9mm spotting rounds are ballistically matched to the rockets and increase the gunner’s first round hit probability.<br>

<h3>Specifications</h3>
<pre>
Maximum effective range
1X2 meter target................................250 meters
Tank-sized target...............................500 meters

Length
To carry........................................29.9 inches
Ready-to-fire...................................54 inches

Weight:
To carry........................................16.6 pounds
Firing with dual purpose rocket.................29.5  pounds
Firing with anti-armor rocket...................30.5 pounds
</pre>
<hr>
<h5>Source - 11th MEU</h5><br>
