<img src="sealusmc.gif" alt= "" align=right align=middle height=145 width=151>
<br><center><h1>RIMPAC 96<BR>Multi-National Force:<br><br>11th Marine Expeditionary Unit</center></h1>
<hr>
<h1>HMMWV</h1>
The High Mobility Multipurpose Wheeled Vehicle (HMMWV) (M-998 truck) provides a variety of wheeled vehicle platforms.  They are:  cargo/troop carrier;  armament carrier;  TOW missile system carrier;  shelter carrier;  and two ambulance variants (2 and 4-litter).  The HMMWV is also the prime mover for the AN/TRC-170 Radio Digital Terminal and the Avenger Missile System.<br>
The M-998 is the baseline vehicle for the M-998 series of 1 1/4-ton trucks.  There are 10 variants of the HMMWV.  They are:  M-998 Cargo/Troop Carrier;  M-1038 Cargo/Troop Carrier;  M-1043 Armament Carrier;  M-1044 Armament Carrier;  M-1045 TOW Carrier;  M-1046 Tow Carrier;  M-997 Ambulance 4-Litter;  M-1035 Ambulance 2-Litter;  M-1037 Shelter Carrier;  M-1042 Shelter Carrier.  All HMMWVs are designed for use over all types of roads, in all weather conditions and are extremely effective in the most difficult terrain.  The HMMWVs high power-to-weight ratio, four wheel drive and high ground clearance  combine to give it outstanding cross-country mobility.<br>
<h3>Specifications</h3>
<pre>
Payload...........................................2,149 to 3,177 lbs
Trailer towing capacity...........................3,400 lbs
Range.............................................300  miles
Crew..............................................2 to 4
Weight............................................5,060 pounds
Length............................................15 feet
Height............................................5.75 feet
                                                  reducible to 4.58 feet
Width.............................................7.08 feet
Engine............................................V8, liquid cooled, 
                                                  compression ignition
Transmission......................................3 speed automatic
Fuel Type.........................................Diesel
Fording depth
Without preparation...............................2.5 feet
With deep water fording kit installed.............5 feet
</pre>
<hr>
<h5>Source - 11th MEU</h5><br>
