<hr>
<h1>5-Ton Truck</h1>
The 5-ton truck provides the primary tactical, medium ground transportation for the Marine Corps and is used by all elements of a Marine Air Ground Task Force.<br>
Marine Corps 5-ton trucks  are used to transport troops, supplies, ammunition, materials, construction items., etc.  Additionally, these trucks tow many types of trailers and artillery guns.<br>
Almost all Marine Corps units are equipped with 5-ton trucks.  The 5-ton truck is available in the following configurations:
<ul>
<li>Cargo			
<li>Dump
<li>Tractor			
<li>Wrecker
</ul>

<h3>Specifications</h3>
<pre>
Payload.......................................10,000 pounds
Max Speed.....................................62 miles per hour
Range.........................................350  miles
Crew..........................................2
Weight........................................21,600 pounds
Length........................................25.6 feet
Height........................................9.73 feet
                                              reducible to 7.6 feet
Width.........................................8.17 feet
Engine........................................6-cylinder, in-line, liquid
                                              cooled, compression ignition
Transmission..................................5 speed automatic
Fuel Type.....................................Diesel
Fording depth
Without preparation...........................30 inches
With deep water fording kit installed.........78 inches
</pre>
