<br><center><h1>RIMPAC 96<BR>Multi-National Force:<br><br>11th Marine Expeditionary Unit</center></h1>
<hr>
<h1>Light Armored Vehicle</h1>
The primary function of the Light Armored Vehicle (LAV) is to provide strategic mobility to reach and engage the threat;  tactical mobility for effective use of firepower;  firepower to defeat soft and armored targets; and battle field survivability to carry out combat missions.<br>
There are six variants of the LAV.  They include:
<ul>
<li>LAV-25;
<li>LAV-C2 (Command and Control);
<li>LAV-AT (Antitank);
<li>LAV-M (Mortar);
<li>LAV-L (Logistics);
<li>and the LAV-R (Recovery).
</ul>
The LAV is an all-terrain, all-weather vehicle with night capabilities.  It is air transportable via KC-130, C-141, and C-5 aircraft, and most importantly to the MEU, CH-53E helicopters.  When combat loaded there are 210 ready rounds and 420 stowed rounds of 25mm ammunition as well as 400 ready rounds and 1,200 stowed rounds of 7.62mm.  There are eight ready rounds and eight stowed rounds  of smoke grenades.  A supplementary M-240G machine gun can be pintle-mounted at the commander’s station in the turret.
The LAV is fully amphibious with a maximum of three minutes preparation.

<h3>Specifications </h3>
<pre>
Troop Capacity...................................Crew plus 6
Max Speed........................................62 miles per hour
Swim Speed.......................................6 miles per hour
Range............................................410 miles
Crew.............................................3 = LAV-25
                                                 7 = LAV-C2
Weight...........................................24,100 pounds
Combat Weight....................................28,200 pounds
Length...........................................20 feet, 11 inches
Height...........................................8 feet, 10 inches
Width............................................8 feet, 2 inches
Armament.........................................M-242 25 mm chain gun,
                                                 M-240 7.62 mm machine
                                                 gun mounted coaxial to
                                                 the main gun.
Communication....................................4 VHF KY-67 
LAV-C2...........................................1 VHF/UHF
                                                 AN/VRC-83
                                                 1 UHF PLRS
                                                 1 HF AN/GRC-213
                                                 1 VHF ANN/PRC-68
</pre>
<hr>
