<br><center><h1>RIMPAC 96<BR>Multi-National Force:<br><br>11th Marine Expeditionary Unit</center></h1>
<hr>
<h1>Assault Amphibious Vehicle</h1>
The Marine Corps AAV7A1 family of assault amphibious vehicles carry the surface assault infantry elements of the landing force and their equipment from amphibious ships to inland objectives.  Once ashore AAV7A1 vehicles support maneuver warfare and perform combat support and combat service support  missions as appropriate.<br>
<br>
There are three AAV variants:
<ul>
<li>	AAVP7A1  —  This is the baseline variant and the primary means of providing armored protected mobility to the Ground Combat Element.  Following closely behind tank units, the AAVP7A1 provides suppressive fires against enemy infantry and lightly armored vehicles.  The AAVP7A1 carries infantry forward to maintain an attack’s momentum; they dismount and remount as the tactical situation requires. 
<li>AAVC7A1  —  This vehicle is used as a mobile command post for infantry regiment and battalion commanders during ship-to-shore movement and operations ashore.
<li>AAVR7A1 —  This version provides recovery and field maintenance support for the AAV7A1 family during operations ashore.
</ul>

<h3>Specifications </h3> 
<pre>
Troop Capacity.....................................21
Cargo Capacity.....................................10,000 pounds
Cruising Speed.....................................20-30 mph (land)
                                                   6 mph (water)
Cruising Range.....................................300 Miles (land)
                                                   7 hours (water)
Crew...............................................3
Weight.............................................57,000 pounds
Prime Contractor...................................FMC Corporation	

<strong>Surfability</strong>
Able to negotiate 6-foot plunging surf combat loaded
and survive 10-foot plunging surf

<strong>Armor</strong>
1.4 to 1.75 inches of aluminum armor plate 

<strong>Armament</strong>
M85 .50 caliber machine gun in the electric drive turret,
or the MK19, MOD 3 40mm machine gun and M2HB .50 caliber machine gun.
</pre>
<hr>
