<br><center><h1>RIMPAC 96<BR>Multi-National Force:<br><br>11th Marine Expeditionary Unit</center></h1>
<hr>
<h1>Landing Craft Air Cushion</h1>
The mission of the Landing Craft Air Cushion (LCAC) is to land heavy vehicles, equipment, personnel, and cargo in an amphibious assault.  The LCAC is a new generation of amphibious assault landing craft.  Combining the heavy lift capability of the surface assault with high speeds of helicopter-borne assault, the LCAC adds a new dimension to the capabilities of amphibious forces.<br>
Capable of traveling over land and water, the LCAC exposes 70 percent of the world’s littoral to amphibious operations.  At over-the-horizon distances of 12 to 100 nautical miles, the LCAC offers Navy and Marine Corps planners another method for attaining surprise when conducting amphibious operations.  Additional flexibility is provided by the LCAC’s ability to operate independent of tides and hydrographic constraints.  Weather can effect LCAC operations, but it is less of a factor than for other ship-to-shore delivery means.<br>
The 11th MEU (SOC) is augmented with five LCACs from Camp Pendleton, Calif.<br>
<h3>Specifications</h3>
<pre>
Troop Capacity................................24
Cargo Capacity................................60 Tons (Design)
..............................................75 Tons (Overload)
Max Speed.....................................40+ Knots
Range.........................................200 Nautical Miles
Crew..........................................5
Propulsion....................................Four TF 40B
                                              Gas Turbines
Length........................................81 feet-off cushion
                                              87 feet, 11 inches-on cushion
Height........................................23 feet 8 inches-on cushion
Width.........................................43 feet 8 inches-off cushion
                                              47 feet-on cushion
</pre>
<hr>
<h5>Source - 11th MEU</h5><br>
