<br><center><h1>RIMPAC 96<BR>Multi-National Force:<br><br>11th Marine Expeditionary Unit</center></h1>
<hr>
<h1>AH-1W Super Cobra</h1>
Missions for the AH-1W Super Cobra Helicopter include:  fire support and security for forward and rear area forces; point target/anti-armor; anti helicopter; armed escort; supporting arms control and coordination; point and limited area air defense from enemy fixed-wing aircraft; and armed and visual reconnaissance.<br>
The Cobra is a day/night   Marine Corps attack helicopter that provides enroute escort for our assault helicopters and their embarked forces.  It is a two-place, tandem-seat, twin engine helicopter capable of land- or sea-based operations.<br>
The MEU’s Aviation Combat Element is reinforced with  four Super Cobras.<br>
The AH-1W is currently being outfitted with a Night Targeting System/Forward Looking Infrared Radar that provides laser rangefinding/designating and camera capabilities.<br>
The Marine Corps deployed four of six active squadrons (48 Cobras) to Southwest Asia during Desert Shield/Storm.  These helicopters destroyed 97 tanks, 104 armored personnel carriers and vehicles, 16 bunkers and two antiaircraft artillery sites without the loss of any aircraft from enemy fire.<br>
<h3>Specifications</h3>
<pre>
Power Plant....................................Two General Electric
                                               T700-GE-401 engines
Max Speed......................................169 miles per hour
Range..........................................294 miles
Crew...........................................2
Max takeoff weight.............................14,750 pounds
Length.........................................58 feet
Height.........................................13.7 feet
Rotor Diameter.................................48 feet
Armament
<ul>
<li>One 20mm turreted cannon with 750 rounds;
<li>four external wing stations that fire
2.75 inch/5.0 inch rockets and a wide variety of
precision guided missiles, to include:
<ul>
<li>TOW/Hellfire (point target/antiarmor)
<li>Sidewinder (antiair)
<li>Sidearm (anti-radar)
</ul>
Manufacturer....................................Bell Helicopter/Textron
</pre>
<hr>
<h5>Source - 11th MEU</h5><br>
