<br><center><h1>RIMPAC 96<BR>Multi-National Force:<br><br>11th Marine Expeditionary Unit</center></h1>
<hr>
<h1>UH-1N Huey Helicopter</h1>
The UH-1N (Huey) helicopter serves a number of missions to include airborne command and control, combat assault, medical evacuation, maritime special operations, supporting arms control and coordination, fire support, and security for forward and rear area forces.
This twin-piloted, twin- engine helicopter provides utility combat helicopter support to the landing force commander during ship-to-shore movement and in subsequent operations ashore.
The aircraft can be outfitted to support operations such as command and control with a specialized communications package, medical evacuation for up to six litter patients and one medical attendant, and search and rescue using a rescue hoist.
Considered to be the most widely used helicopter in the world, with more than 9,000 produced from the 1950s to the present, the Huey is flown today by approximately 40 countries.
The 11th MEU(SOC)'s ACE is reinforced with three Huey’s.
SPECIFICATIONS

<pre>
Payload........................................13 passengers -or-
                                               6 liter patients
                                               with 1 medical
                                               attendant
Max Speed......................................139 miles-per-hour
Range..........................................197 miles 
Crew...........................................4
Max takeoff weight.............................10,500 pounds 
Length.........................................57 feet
Height.........................................15 feet
Rotor Diameter.................................48 feet

Armament
<ul>
<li>M-240 (7.62mm) machine gun or the GAU-16 (.50 caliber) machine gun
or the GAU-17 (7.62mm) automatic gun.  All three weapons systems are
crew-served and the GAU-2B/A can be controlled by the pilot
in the fixed forward firing mode.  The Huey can also carry two
7-shot or 19-shot 2.75" rocket pods
</ul>
Manufacturer...................................Bell Helicopter/Textron
</pre>
<hr>
<h5>Source - 11th MEU</h5><br>
