<body background="chalk.jpg">
<img src="rimpac3.gif" alt= "" align=left align=middle height=145 width=190>
<img src="sealusmc.gif" alt= "" align=right align=middle height=145 width=151>
<br><center><h1>RIMPAC 96<BR>Multi-National Force:<br><br>11th Marine Expeditionary Unit</center></h1>
<hr>
<h1>Ch-53E Super Stallion</h1>
The mission of the CH-53E Super Stallion is to provide helicopter transport support of supplies, equipment, and personnel  for the landing force during ship-to-shore movement and within the objective area.  This shipboard compatible helicopter is an assault support aircraft that can be employed for the internal lift and movement of cargo, for the recovery of tactical aircraft and for the external lift of weapons and equipment.<br> 
The CH-53E is the free world’s largest helicopter.  Utilizing three engines, the CH-53E is rated at 16 tons of lift.  The Super Stallion can lift 93 percent of all heavy equipment in a Marine division compared to the older CH-53D Sea Stallion’s 38 percent.<br>
The 53E is also equipped with a refueling probe, an improvement from the 53D, and can be refueled in flight.<br>

<h3>Specifications</h3>
<pre>
Payload...........................37 passengers normal configuration
                                  55 with centerline seats installed
Max Speed.........................172 miles per hour
Range.............................621 miles (without refueling)
                                  Indefinite with aerial refueling
Crew..............................3
Maximum takeoff weight............69,750 pounds (Internal weight)
                                  73,500 pounds (External load)
Length............................99 feet, 5 inches
Height............................28 feet, 4 inches
Rotor Diameter....................79 feet
Armament..........................Two XM-218 .50 caliber
                                  machine guns
Manufacturer......................Sikorsky Aircraft
</pre>
<hr>
<h5>Source - 11th MEU</h5><br>
