<body background="chalk.jpg">
<img src="rimpac3.gif" alt= "" align=left align=middle height=145 width=190>
<img src="sealusmc.gif" alt= "" align=right align=middle height=145 width=151>
<br><center><h1>RIMPAC 96<BR>Multi-National Force:<br><br>11th Marine Expeditionary Unit</center></h1>
<hr>
<h1>AV-8B Harrier</h1>
The AV-8B Harrier II is a single-engine, one-seat aircraft capable of vertical/short take-offs and landings which may be used as a fighter or in an attack role.  The AV-8B may be used to escort helicopters, conduct close and deep combat air support and fly offensive missions against enemy ground-to-air defenses.<br>
Three AV-8B squadrons stationed approximately 40 miles (64 kilometers) from the Kuwaiti border, were the most forward deployed tactical strike aircraft during Operation Desert Storm and operated from relatively unprepared sites.<br>
One Harrier squadron and a six aircraft detachment operated off the landing helicopter ship USS NASSAU in the Persian Gulf during Desert Storm.  The average turnaround time during the ground war surge was 23 minutes.<br>
The night attack version of the AV-8B became operational in the summer of 1991.<br>
<h3>Specifications</h3>
<pre>
Speed..................................629 miles per hour
Crew...................................1
Propulsion.............................One Rolls Royce
                                       F402-RR-406/208
Ceiling................................50,000 feet
Length.................................46 feet 4 inches
Wingspan...............................30 feet 4 inches
Height.................................11 feet 9 inches
Weight.................................12,000 pounds empty
                                       29,750 pounds maximum
                                       gross take-off
Armament...............................Wing points for AIM-9 Sidewinder
                                       and an assortment of air-to-ground
                                       weapons and AGM-65
                                       Maverick missiles
Contractor.............................Mcdonnell Douglas
Cost...................................$23.7 million
</pre>
<hr>
