<html>

<title>CO, USS ()</title>

<body background="chalk.jpg">
<img src="subpac.gif" alt=""ALIGN=RIGHT width=250 height=312></h1>
<h1>William D. French<br>
Commander, USN</h1>
<h2>Commanding Officer,<br>
USS SALT LAKE CITY (SSN 716)</h2>
Commander French graduated with a Bachelors Degree in Mechanical Engineering from Vanderbilt University and was commissioned through the Navy Reserve Officer Training Corps program in May 1979.  After graduation, he completed Naval Nuclear Power School in Orlando, Florida and nuclear prototype training in Ballots Spa, New York.<br>
Following completion of the Submarine Officer's Basic Course at the Naval Submarine School in Groton, Connecticut he reported for duty in USS SPADEFISH (SSN 668) Norfolk, Virginia.  From November 1980 to February 1984, he served as Sonar Office and Damage Control Assistant and completed submarine qualification.  From March 1984 until march 1986, Commander French attended Naval Postgraduate School in Monterey, California where he received a Master of Science degree in Systems Technology.<br>
Commander French attended the Submarine Officer's Advanced Course in Gronton Connecticut and reported in September 1986 to USS SEA DEVIL (SSN 664) in Charleston, South Carolina as the Operations Officer.  During his tour, SEA DEVIL participated in the first three ships international surfacing at the North Pole.  He transferred in November 1988 to USS TECUMSEH (SSBN 628) (GOLD) where he served as Engineer Officer and qualified for command of nuclear submarines.  He was relieved as Executive Officer in USS HELENA (SSN 725) in Pearl Harbor, Hawaii in March 1991.  From November 1992 to March 1995 he served as the Nuclear Officer Program Manager at the Bureau of Naval Personnel in Washington, D. C.<br>
Commander French assumed command of USS SALT LAKE CITY (SSN 716) on December 8, 1995.<br>
Commander French is married to the former Monika Daniels of Memphis, Tennessee.  They currently live in Coronado.  California with their son, Thomas.  Commander French's personal awards include the Meritorious Service Medal (two awards).  Naval Commendation Medal (four awards) and Navy Achievement Medal (two awards).<br>
<br>
<br>
