<html>

<title>CO, USS KAHMEHAMEHA (SSN 642)</title>

<body background="chalk.jpg">
<img src="subpac.gif" alt=""ALIGN=RIGHT width=200 height=215></h1>
<h1>Howard F. Reese<br>
Commander, USN</h1>
<h2>Commanding Officer,<br>
USS KAMEHAMEHA (SSN 642)</h2>
Commander Howard F. Reese is the son of Bruce and Margaret Reese and a native of Cincinnati, Ohio.  He is a 1978 graduate of Miami University in Oxford, Ohio where he earned a Bachelor of Science degree in Engineering Technology, and was commissioned through the Naval Reserve Officer Training Corps program.<br>
After completing nuclear power training in Orlando, FL and Idaho Falls, ID, Commander Reese reported to USS BILLFISH (SSN 676) where he served as Main Propulsion Assistant and Damage Control Assistant until May 1983.  He returned to Idaho Falls, ID for his first tour ashore as an instructor at the Naval Nuclear Power Training Unit.  In January 1987, he returned to sea for his Department Head tour on USS SHARK (SSN 591) where he served as Engineer Officer until September 1990.  In December 1990, he reported as Executive Officer on USS GEORGIA (SSBN 719)(Gold).  In December 1992, he rotated ashore and completed an assignment on the staff of Submarine Development Squadron Twelve.  On 19 May 1995, he relieved as Commanding Officer, USS KAMEHAMEHA (SSN 642).<br>
Commander Reese is authorized to wear the Meritorious Service Medal, Navy Commendation Medal with one gold star, Navy Achievement Medal with three gold stars, and several unit and service awards.<br>
Commander Reese, his wife Doren, and their children, Jackson, Kacee, Clinton, Paul, and Matthew reside in Pearl Harbor, Hawaii.<br>
<br>
<br>
