<html>

<title>CO,HMAS NEWCASTLE (FFG 06)</title>

<body background="chalk.jpg">
<h1>Commander Nigel Antony Perry CSC, RAN
</h1>
<h2>Commanding Officer, HMAS NEWCASTLE</h2>

<strong>Date and Place of Birth:</strong> 20th February 1957, Imtarfa, Malta<br>
<strong>Sports and Interests:</strong> Tennis, Golf, Kayaking and Woodwork<br><br>
<strong>SERVICE CAREER</strong><br>
Commander Nigel Perry joined the Navy as a 15 year old Junior Entry at RANC.  After completing Midshipman training onboard MELBOURNE and VENDFTTA he gained his     Bridge Watchkeeping Certificate and served as an Officer of the Watch onhoard VAMPIRE.  This was followed by 3 years in the Amphibious Squadron in a number of sea-going and staff positions.<br>
Commander Perry completed Assistant Principle Warfare Officers' Course at WATSON and PWO course in the UK specialising in Anti - Submarine Warfare, serving as the Communications Officer of SWAN and ASW Officer of CANBERRA.  This was followed by staff positions in the Directorate of Underwater Warfare and as the PWO career manager in the Directorate of Naval Officers' Postings.<br>
Service as the Executive Officer of HMAS SYDNEY 1989-1991 included deployments to South East Asia and around the world and to the Persian Gulf during the war against Iraq, following which he was awarded the Conspicuous Service Cross.  Commander Perry then served 3 1/2 years as the operations and exercise planner on the Maritime Commander's staff prior to taking command of NEWCASTLE on 08 May 95.  Commander Perry is married to Annette and has two daughters, Nichola (9) and Ashlea (7).<br>
<br>
<br>
