<html>
<head>
<title>
USS INDEPENDENCE (CV 62) - Commanding Officer
</title>
</head>
<body>
<center><img src="co.jpg"></a><br> <br>
<h2>CAPT David P. Polatty III</h2>
<h2>Commanding Officer<br>
USS INDEPENDENCE (CV 62)</h2>
</center>
<br>
<p> Captain David P. Polatty III was born in Annapolis, Maryland.  A graduate of Granby High School in Norfolk, Virginia, he enlisted in the U.S. Navy in 1966 before attending the Naval Academy Preparatory School.  He graduated from the U.S. Naval Academy in June 1971. </p>


<p> Captain Polatty's first assignment was as First Lieutenant aboard the USS HOLDER (DD 819).  During this tour, HOLDER deployed to the Mediterranean with USS INDEPENDENCE (CV 62).  Following this tour, he entered flight training, and was designated a Naval Flight Officer in August 1972. 


<p> After Fleet Replacement Training in the all-weather, medium attack A-6 "Intruder" with Attack Squadron 42, Captain Polatty made two Mediterranean deployments with Attack Squadron 75 aboard USS SARATOGA (CV 60).  From there, he transferred back to VA-42 where he served as a flight instructor.  His next tour was with Attack Squadron 34 deploying to the Mediterranean aboard USS JOHN F. KENNEDY (CV 67). </p>


<p> In November 1980, Captain Polatty attended the U.S. Naval War College, graduating with highest distinction in 1981.  He then served as Aide and Executive Assistant to the President, Naval War College. </p>


<p> In April 1983, Captain Polatty reported as Operations Officer of Carrier Air Wing EIGHT, deploying to the Mediterranean aboard USS NIMITZ (CVN 68).  In May 1985, he joined the staff of Commander Naval Air Force, U.S. Atlantic Fleet, as the Medium Attack Readiness Officer. </p>


<p> Captain Polatty served as Executive Officer, then Commanding Officer, of Attack Squadron 115 from November 1986 to November 1989.  Forward deployed to Japan, the "Eagles" embarked in USS MIDWAY (CV 41).  Reporting as Deputy Commander, Carrier Air Wing ONE in May 1990, Captain Polatty flew combat missions in support of Operation DESERT STORM from USS AMERICA (CV 66) while operating in both the Red Sea and Arabian Gulf. </p>


<p> From March 1992 to January 1994, Captain Polatty commanded USS MILWAUKEE (AOR 2).  During this tour, MILWAUKEE was awarded the Battle "E" and Meritorious Unit Commendation.  From February to July 1994, Captain Polatty attended the NATO Defense College in Rome, Italy.  Captain Polatty took command of USS INDEPENDENCE (CV 62) January 25, 1995.</p>


<p> Captain Polatty has been selected for promotion to Rear Admiral. His awards include the Legion of Merit, Distinguished Flying Cross with Combat "V" (2 awards), Bronze Star, Meritorious Service Medal (3 awards), Air Medal with Combat "V" (1 individual, 2 strike/flight awards), Navy Commendation Medal with Combat "V" (2 awards), and various unit and campaign awards. </p>


<p> Captain Polatty is married to the former Nancy Jane Holland of Virginia Beach, Virginia.  They have two sons, David, a Navy Lieutenant, and Ryan, a Virginia Tech student. </p>


<br><br>
