<head>
<title>
USS INDEPENDENCE (CV 62) - Executive Officer
</title>
</head>
<center><img src="xo.jpg"></a><br> <br>
<h2>CAPT Hartmann J. Kircher, IV</h2>
<h2>Executive Officer<br>
USS INDEPENDENCE (CV 62)</h2>
</center>
<br>
<p> Captain Kircher comes from Sparta, New Jersey and is a graduate of Tennessee Wesleyan college.  He received his commission as a Naval Officer through the Aviation Reserve Officer Candidate (AVROC) program in August 1974 and was designated a Naval Aviator in September 1975.  In April 1976, upon completion of readiness training in the SH-3H at Helicopter Antisubmarine Squadron ONE (HS-1), he reported to Helicopter Antisubmarine Squadron FIFTEEN (HS-15) embarked in USS AMERICA (CV 66). </p>

<p>In July 1978, Captain Kircher reported to Training Squadron TWENTY-SEVEN (VT-27) as an instructor pilot flying the T-28 "Trojan."  His next assignment was with the "Night Owls" of Training Squadron THIRTY-ONE (VT-31) as the T-44 Model Manager and NATOPS evaluator.  Captain Kircher returned to sea duty as Navigator aboard USS TARAWA (LHA 1).  After completing a WESTPAC deployment and contingency operations with the Multi-National Peace Keeping force in Beirut, Lebanon, he was assigned as an instructor pilot with Helicopter Antisubmarine Squadron TEN (HS-10) at North Island, California.  In 1986 he transferred to Helicopter Antisubmarine Squadron TWELVE (HS-12) as the Maintenance Officer and completed several WESTPAC deployments while embarked in USS MIDWAY (CV 41). </p>

<p>In February 1989, Captain Kircher reported to the Office of the Chief of Naval Operations, Officer Plans and Policy where he served as the Head, Officer Promotion Plans (OP-130F).  After a brief period of refresher training in Helicopter Antisubmarine Squadron ONE (HS-1), he reported as Executive Officer of Helicopter Antisubmarine Squadron FIVE (HS-5) in February 1991 and assumed command of the "Nightdippers" in May 1992.  In November 1993 he reported to the Naval War College at Newport, R.I. and received a Master's Degree in Strategic Studies and National Security Affairs.  Captain Kircher reported to his current assignment as Executive Officer of USS INDPENDENCE (CV 62) in May of 1995.  To date he has accumulated over 4,600 flight hours in various military aircraft. </p>

<p>Captain Kircher's awards include the Meritorious Service Medal (two awards), the Navy Commendation Medal and several other personal, unit and expeditionary awards.  Captain Kircher is married to Commander Karen L. Kircher, U.S. Navy (Retired) of Grand Rapids, Michigan.  They have one son, Hartmann, and reside in Yokosuka, Japan. </p>
<br><br>
