<head>
<title>
USS INDEPENDENCE (CV 62) - Command Master Chief
</title>
</head>
<body>
<center> <img src="cmc.jpg"></a><br>
<h2>MMCM(SS) Ashley K. Dwiggins</h2>
<h2>Command Master Chief<br>
USS INDEPENDENCE (CV 62)</h2><br></center>


<p>Master Chief Dwiggins was born 15 September 1950 in Winston-
Salem, North Carolina.  He graduated from Groveton High School in 
Fairfax, Virginia, attended George Mason College for one year, and 
enlisted in the Navy in July 1970. </p>

<p>Sent to Recruit Training Center in Great Lakes, Illinois, 
Master Chief Dwiggins remained there and completed Basic Propulsion 
and Engineering School, then Machinist's Mate "A" School.  He 
subsequently attended Nuclear Power School at Bainbridge, Maryland, 
and the S1C Nuclear Power Training Unit (NTPU) at Windsor, 
Connecticut.  Following completion of Submarine School in Groton, 
Connecticut in June 1972, he reported to USS ULYSSES S. GRANT 
(SSBN 631BLUE) in Charleston, South Carolina, where he qualified up 
through Engineering Watch Supervisor. The ship deployed out of Holy 
Loch, Scotland.  In September 1976 he was again assigned to the S1C 
NTPU, where he served as a Crew Leading Petty Officer and qualified Engineering Officer of the Watch, and was then selected to the Staff Trainging Group. He was also advanced to Chief Petty Officer prior to transfer in October 1979.  Serving as Machinery Division LCPO, he was advanced to Senior Chief Petty Officer and moved up as Engineering Department Enlisted Advisor (EDEA) on board USS SWORDFISH (SSN 579), home ported in Pearl Harbor, Hawaii.  In 
November 1984 Senior Chief Dwiggins transferred to Naval 
Submarine Training Center Pacific and served as the Ford Island 
Senior Instructor and advanced to Master Chief Petty Officer in 
1986.  In August 1987 he reported to USS HAWKBILL (SSN 666) as EDEA 
and qualified as Diving Officer of the Watch.  He then transferred 
to USS OLYMPIA (SSN 717) as Chief of the Boat. Leaving Hawaii in 
June 1993 he reported as Command Master Chief to TRIDENT Refit 
Facility in Bangor, Washington.  While there, he was selected to 
participate in both the 1994 and 1995 Chief Petty Officer 
Selection Boards.  Master Chief Dwiggins attended the Senior 
Enlisted Academy from August to October 1995 where he achieved an 
Academic Excellence Award and was selected as the Honor Graduate of 
Class 68. </p>

<p>In November 1995, Master Chief Dwiggins reported to the Navy's 
only forward deployed aircraft carrier and oldest ship in the navy, 
the USS INDEPENDENCE (CV 62), home ported in Yokosuka, Japan, where he 
is currently serving as Command Master Chief. </p>


<p>Master Chief Dwiggins' awards include the Navy Commendation 
Medal five awards, Navy Achievement Medal two awards, Good Conduct Medal six awards, Navy Expeditionary Medal, and National Defense Service Medal two awards. </p>

<p>Master Chief Dwiggins is married to the former Sharon Lee 
Paternoster of Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania.  They have six sons and 
one daughter with ages ranging from three to twenty-four years old, 
and all are currently living in Hawaii. </p>



