<head>
<title>
Carrier Air Wing FIVE - Commander
</title>
</head>
<body>
<center><img src="cag.jpg"></a><br>
<h2>CAPT Brian M. Calhoun<br><br>
Commander<br>
Carrier Air Wing FIVE<br></h2>
<br>
</center>

<p>Captain Brian M. Calhoun was born 28 February 1946 in London, England.  He was raised in Wisconsin and is a graduate of the University of Wisconsin, Class of 1970. </p>

<p>Entering the Navy in 1972 as an enlisted man, he attended Air Traffic Controllman "A" School at Naval Air Station Glynco, Georgia.  Upon graduation he entered the Aviation Officer Candidate (AOC) Program.  He later received his "Wings of Gold" on 23 September 1973 in Beeville, Texas. </p>

<p>His initial assignment was to VC-2 at Naval Air Station Oceana, Virginia flying A-4s.  Fleet tours have been with VF-74 in the F-4J and VFAs 125, 132, 106 and 15 in the F/A-18.  Staff tours have been as Aide and Flag Lieutenant to Commander Naval Air Force, U.S. Atlantic Fleet and as F/A-18 Requirements Officer for the Chief of Naval Operations. </p>

<p>Combat cruises include participation in Operation ELDORADO CANYON in Libya and as Commanding Officer of VFA-15 during Operation DESERT STORM in Iraq. </p>

<p>On 7 June 1993, Captain Calhoun reported for duty to Carrier Air Wing FIVE as Deputy Commander and subsequently assumed command as Commander, Carrier Air Wing FIVE on 13 July 1994. </p>

<p>Captain Calhoun has flown more than 6,000 tactical jet flight hours, including more than 3,900 in the F/A-18 aircraft, and has over 1,000 carrier landings.  His personal awards include the Bronze Star, Meritorious Service Medal (second award, Individual Air Medal with Bronze Star and Combat "V", Strike Flight Air Medal (second award), Navy Commendation Medal with combat "V" and various unit and campaign awards. </p>

<p>He is married to the former Jeannie Knight of Green Cove Springs, Florida.  Captain and Mrs. Calhoun reside at Naval Air Facility Atsugi, Japan. </p>

<br><br>
