<html> <title> ADA Compliance Guide Specialty Chapters--Self Evaluations</title>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/tpg/gif/tpgpattern.gif">

<center><IMG SRC="/tpg/person/able/ablehead.gif" alt="ADA Compliance
Guide"></center>
<P>
<h2>ADA Compliance Guide Specialty Chapters--Self Evaluations</h2>
<body>
Throughout the "specialty" chapters, sample self-evaluations contain questions
entities may use when reviewing their compliance with the ADA.<P>

For example, in the public works and housing chapter, when reviewing ongoing
compliance in providing accessible housing, entities are encouraged to consider,
among other things, how they will:<P>

<UL>
<LI>train physical operations and maintenance staff to be aware of structural
barriers that may exist now or in the future; and<P>

<LI>ensure that appropriate signs are posted whenever a barrier removal activity
is completed.</UL><P>

In the chapter on banking, a self-evaluation on teller activities is provided for
reviewing such potential problem areas as:<P>

<UL><LI>the location and number of teller stations, windows or counters;<P>

<LI>the services and products provided by tellers; and<P>

<LI>how tellers interact with customers.</UL><P>

In the public schools chapter, some suggested questions for reviewing food
services include consideration of:<P>

<UL><LI>the location and services provided at each cafeteria in school districts;<P>

<LI>the furnishings and layout of the dining area(s); and<P>

<LI>areas where program accessibility does not exist and ways to achieve it.</UL><P>

</body> 

